WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.372 --> 00:00:06.907
 The world economy in

00:00:06.907 --> 00:00:11.178
crisis. Europe in shock.

00:00:11.178 --> 00:00:13.714
Riots, mass unemployment,

00:00:13.714 --> 00:00:15.115
extreme parties on the

00:00:15.115 --> 00:00:18.952
march. It was not supposed

00:00:18.952 --> 00:00:22.122
to be this way. After the

00:00:22.122 --> 00:00:23.757
war, the European Union

00:00:23.757 --> 00:00:25.092
was built to secure

00:00:25.092 --> 00:00:26.727
cooperation, prosperity,

00:00:26.727 --> 00:00:28.929
and peace in Europe. And

00:00:28.929 --> 00:00:30.564
later, a common currency

00:00:30.564 --> 00:00:33.600
was introduced, the Euro.

00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:35.202
It resulted in a long

00:00:35.202 --> 00:00:37.170
boom, but it ended in a

00:00:37.170 --> 00:00:39.172
spectacular bust.

00:00:40.974 --> 00:00:42.976
Where did Europe go wrong?

00:00:46.146 --> 00:00:48.482
And is the United States right

00:00:48.482 --> 00:00:49.483
now repeating the

00:00:49.483 --> 00:00:52.119
same mistakes?

00:01:00.994 --> 00:01:02.996
Hello, I'm Johan Norberg.

00:01:02.996 --> 00:01:04.431
And this is Malmo...Sweden,

00:01:04.431 --> 00:01:07.534
my hometown. If we had

00:01:07.534 --> 00:01:08.535
been standing here in the

00:01:08.535 --> 00:01:09.703
Middle Ages, we'd be

00:01:09.703 --> 00:01:11.338
looking at 	the busy piers

00:01:11.338 --> 00:01:12.906
of the waterfront.

00:01:12.906 --> 00:01:14.274
It would be lined with ships

00:01:14.274 --> 00:01:16.777
right here. In the 14th

00:01:16.777 --> 00:01:17.978
century those ships could

00:01:17.978 --> 00:01:19.780
carry more than 30,000

00:01:19.780 --> 00:01:21.315
barrels of herring,

00:01:21.315 --> 00:01:22.316
carried to different

00:01:22.316 --> 00:01:24.017
European ports in a single

00:01:24.017 --> 00:01:26.253
year. At that time, Malmo

00:01:26.253 --> 00:01:28.088
was part of the Hanseatic

00:01:28.088 --> 00:01:29.623
League, an economic union

00:01:29.623 --> 00:01:30.891
of cities not unlike

00:01:30.891 --> 00:01:33.193
today's European Union.

00:01:33.193 --> 00:01:34.795
By the 16th century, Malmo

00:01:34.795 --> 00:01:36.096
was known throughout

00:01:36.096 --> 00:01:37.531
northern Europe as a city

00:01:37.531 --> 00:01:38.832
of savvy business energy,

00:01:38.832 --> 00:01:40.200
and of a commitment to

00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:42.636
commerce.  No one better

00:01:42.636 --> 00:01:43.637
represented the

00:01:43.637 --> 00:01:44.671
entrepreneurial spirit of

00:01:44.671 --> 00:01:47.074
Malmo than Jorgen Kock.

00:01:47.074 --> 00:01:48.675
In the 16th century, he was a

00:01:48.675 --> 00:01:50.277
very successful banker and

00:01:50.277 --> 00:01:51.845
trader...and the mayor of

00:01:51.845 --> 00:01:57.050
Malmo. This building was

00:01:57.050 --> 00:01:58.452
Jorgen Kock's home, and

00:01:58.452 --> 00:01:59.453
the center of his vast

00:01:59.453 --> 00:02:00.954
business operations. He

00:02:00.954 --> 00:02:02.689
even had his bank there up

00:02:02.689 --> 00:02:05.292
on the second floor.

00:02:05.292 --> 00:02:06.393
Now it's a restaurant and a

00:02:06.393 --> 00:02:08.061
conference center.

00:02:08.061 --> 00:02:09.997
This place...and this city

00:02:09.997 --> 00:02:10.998
represents the

00:02:10.998 --> 00:02:12.265
entrepreneurship and the

00:02:12.265 --> 00:02:13.600
international trade that

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:14.601
once made Europe

00:02:14.601 --> 00:02:16.737
prosperous. So, it makes

00:02:16.737 --> 00:02:18.305
it an ideal place to hold

00:02:18.305 --> 00:02:20.173
a conference on the crisis

00:02:20.173 --> 00:02:21.475
that is now shaking the

00:02:21.475 --> 00:02:23.877
world. Don Boudreaux, an

00:02:23.877 --> 00:02:24.978
economist from the United

00:02:24.978 --> 00:02:26.813
States and I have invited

00:02:26.813 --> 00:02:27.814
some of the world's

00:02:27.814 --> 00:02:29.249
leading young thinkers.

00:02:29.249 --> 00:02:31.385
They're here for a couple

00:02:31.385 --> 00:02:33.353
days discussing the

00:02:33.353 --> 00:02:34.688
reasons for the crisis

00:02:34.688 --> 00:02:35.689
that is now affecting

00:02:35.689 --> 00:02:37.190
Europe; the potential for

00:02:37.190 --> 00:02:38.358
that crisis to affect the

00:02:38.358 --> 00:02:40.227
United States, and how it

00:02:40.227 --> 00:02:41.228
might affect the

00:02:41.228 --> 00:02:43.230
day-to-day lives of all of us.

00:03:04.985 --> 00:03:05.986
The whole debt crisis

00:03:05.986 --> 00:03:09.423
started in Greece.

00:03:09.423 --> 00:03:10.424
Is there more involved than

00:03:10.424 --> 00:03:11.992
financial stability?

00:03:13.393 --> 00:03:14.394
Well, there's no connection

00:03:14.394 --> 00:03:15.796
between the people of

00:03:15.796 --> 00:03:17.798
Greece and the politicians.

00:03:18.999 --> 00:03:21.501
Every rule has been broken,

00:03:21.501 --> 00:03:23.503
every rule has been broken.

00:03:25.806 --> 00:03:26.773
We've all seen the stories, or

00:03:26.773 --> 00:03:28.809
read the newspaper reports.

00:03:28.809 --> 00:03:29.543
Are the conclusions

00:03:29.543 --> 00:03:31.011
we draw from them

00:03:31.011 --> 00:03:33.013
universal?

00:03:34.214 --> 00:03:35.449
Now, you gentlemen

00:03:35.782 --> 00:03:36.783
have discussed the economic

00:03:36.783 --> 00:03:39.786
and financial aspects of the

00:03:39.786 --> 00:03:41.455
debt crisis. I wanted to touch

00:03:41.455 --> 00:03:43.457
upon another subject,

00:03:43.457 --> 00:03:44.458
namely the consequences

00:03:44.458 --> 00:03:46.960
for freedom and democracy,

00:03:46.960 --> 00:03:48.195
essentially those values

00:03:48.195 --> 00:03:49.930
that the EU is supposed to

00:03:49.930 --> 00:03:51.264
safeguard. I mean, and now

00:03:51.264 --> 00:03:52.265
we see that with the

00:03:52.265 --> 00:03:53.633
fiscal compact, and the

00:03:53.633 --> 00:03:55.402
moves towards even deeper

00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:57.137
political integration that

00:03:57.137 --> 00:03:58.171
the powers of national

00:03:58.171 --> 00:03:59.172
parliaments- and

00:03:59.172 --> 00:04:00.474
ultimately citizens to

00:04:00.474 --> 00:04:02.542
influence the EU is

00:04:02.542 --> 00:04:05.479
diminished, and I think

00:04:05.479 --> 00:04:06.913
that will create a

00:04:06.913 --> 00:04:07.714
backlash that will make it

00:04:07.714 --> 00:04:09.549
difficult to manage the

00:04:09.549 --> 00:04:11.651
situation. Would it be

00:04:11.651 --> 00:04:14.087
better like to have

00:04:14.087 --> 00:04:15.589
measures take now, rather

00:04:15.589 --> 00:04:17.991
than postponing it?

00:04:17.991 --> 00:04:19.059
Particularly in Southern

00:04:19.059 --> 00:04:20.760
Europe, you will lose

00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:22.229
political support for the

00:04:22.229 --> 00:04:23.296
measures that need to go

00:04:23.296 --> 00:04:24.498
through. And I think what

00:04:24.498 --> 00:04:25.499
you are going to see is

00:04:25.499 --> 00:04:26.566
the rise of nationalist

00:04:26.566 --> 00:04:27.701
movements, of the left and

00:04:27.701 --> 00:04:28.702
the right. You see that in

00:04:28.702 --> 00:04:29.703
Greece now. You see Greece

00:04:29.703 --> 00:04:30.704
might become the norm;

00:04:30.704 --> 00:04:31.705
first for Italy, for

00:04:31.705 --> 00:04:32.706
Spain, for Portugal.

00:04:32.706 --> 00:04:33.707
I mean...even in Austria,

00:04:33.707 --> 00:04:35.475
for example. Levels of

00:04:35.475 --> 00:04:36.943
hostility to the European

00:04:36.943 --> 00:04:38.478
Union are now running at

00:04:38.478 --> 00:04:40.180
close to 50 percent.

00:04:40.180 --> 00:04:41.748
So those values of freedom

00:04:41.748 --> 00:04:45.585
of democracy are not as old

00:04:45.585 --> 00:04:46.453
everywhere in Europe as

00:04:46.453 --> 00:04:47.988
we'd like to think, and

00:04:47.988 --> 00:04:49.990
should not be taken for granted.

00:04:49.990 --> 00:04:50.991
Also, I think

00:04:50.991 --> 00:04:52.659
that the concept of

00:04:52.659 --> 00:04:53.460
liberty in the European

00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:56.763
Union has been skewed from

00:04:56.763 --> 00:05:00.967
a focus on basic freedoms

00:05:00.967 --> 00:05:02.802
towards a much more

00:05:02.802 --> 00:05:04.171
expansive concept of

00:05:04.171 --> 00:05:05.438
freedom. If you look at the

00:05:05.438 --> 00:05:06.473
Charter of Fundamental Rights,

00:05:06.473 --> 00:05:07.974
for instance - it does not

00:05:07.974 --> 00:05:09.342
only protect

00:05:09.342 --> 00:05:10.177
freedom of expression, and

00:05:10.177 --> 00:05:11.545
these values...it also

00:05:11.545 --> 00:05:13.513
protects consumer protection,

00:05:13.513 --> 00:05:14.981
social security,

00:05:14.981 --> 00:05:16.183
and all these things

00:05:16.183 --> 00:05:17.484
and you see that

00:05:17.484 --> 00:05:19.286
European courts are now

00:05:19.286 --> 00:05:20.120
starting to make decisions

00:05:20.120 --> 00:05:23.924
that could result in

00:05:23.924 --> 00:05:25.292
austerity measures being

00:05:25.292 --> 00:05:26.126
declared a violation of

00:05:26.126 --> 00:05:28.128
human rights.

00:05:31.998 --> 00:05:34.768
The whole debt crisis started in

00:05:34.768 --> 00:05:36.603
Greece...the canary in the

00:05:36.603 --> 00:05:38.605
coal mine... if you will.

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:41.608
I went there to see what

00:05:41.608 --> 00:05:43.009
might be in store for the

00:05:43.009 --> 00:05:45.011
rest of us.	

00:05:46.012 --> 00:05:47.013
The Greek government

00:05:47.013 --> 00:05:48.014
falsified the

00:05:48.014 --> 00:05:50.016
public account to make it

00:05:50.016 --> 00:05:51.918
into the Euro. And as a

00:05:51.918 --> 00:05:52.919
Euro member, they had

00:05:52.919 --> 00:05:53.920
access to the European

00:05:53.920 --> 00:05:55.622
credit card- so they could

00:05:55.622 --> 00:05:56.823
borrow even more.

00:05:56.823 --> 00:05:59.059
They even lied about the

00:05:59.059 --> 00:05:59.960
budget deficits to their

00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:02.295
own people! But at the

00:06:02.295 --> 00:06:03.296
same time, it made it possible

00:06:03.296 --> 00:06:04.965
for them to buy votes

00:06:04.965 --> 00:06:06.766
by increasing wages; by

00:06:06.766 --> 00:06:09.869
increasing public spending.

00:06:09.869 --> 00:06:10.870
When these lies

00:06:10.870 --> 00:06:12.305
were exposed, the

00:06:12.305 --> 00:06:13.306
lenders didn't want to

00:06:13.306 --> 00:06:14.641
lend more to Greece and

00:06:14.641 --> 00:06:15.775
the politicians had to

00:06:15.775 --> 00:06:16.109
tell the voters that,

00:06:16.109 --> 00:06:18.645
"We are out of money." At this

00:06:18.645 --> 00:06:20.981
point- people reacted and

00:06:20.981 --> 00:06:23.049
protested, but not against

00:06:23.049 --> 00:06:24.618
spending, but against

00:06:24.618 --> 00:06:26.186
paying for it. So instead,

00:06:26.186 --> 00:06:27.754
they've started supporting

00:06:27.754 --> 00:06:29.322
extremist parties;

00:06:29.322 --> 00:06:32.325
providing simple solutions

00:06:32.325 --> 00:06:33.393
and blaming the usual

00:06:33.393 --> 00:06:34.961
scapegoats. It's always

00:06:34.961 --> 00:06:37.063
nice to be able to have

00:06:37.063 --> 00:06:39.065
your cake and eat it, too-

00:06:39.099 --> 00:06:40.100
and send the bill to

00:06:40.100 --> 00:06:44.571
somebody else. 

00:06:44.571 --> 00:06:46.139
Diomidus Spinellis is a

00:06:46.139 --> 00:06:47.607
computer engineer whom the

00:06:47.607 --> 00:06:49.175
government turned to-

00:06:49.175 --> 00:06:52.812
to reform the tax system.

00:06:52.812 --> 00:06:53.813
I was very optimistic...

00:06:53.813 --> 00:06:54.814
because all I could

00:06:54.814 --> 00:06:55.815
see around me was

00:06:55.815 --> 00:06:57.317
low-hanging fruits; things

00:06:57.317 --> 00:06:58.818
I could see that you just

00:06:58.818 --> 00:06:59.619
have to lift your hand and

00:06:59.619 --> 00:07:00.587
pick them and you can make

00:07:00.587 --> 00:07:02.622
a change. Many of those

00:07:02.622 --> 00:07:04.958
low-hanging fruits are

00:07:04.958 --> 00:07:05.959
still here after two and a

00:07:05.959 --> 00:07:06.960
half years...

00:07:06.960 --> 00:07:08.962
and this makes me sad.

00:07:12.966 --> 00:07:14.934
Revolt in order to find

00:07:14.934 --> 00:07:16.436
something better...from the

00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:18.972
annual policy in Greece.

00:07:18.972 --> 00:07:19.973
Have you lost faith in

00:07:19.973 --> 00:07:24.377
the politicians? Yes...yes.

00:07:24.377 --> 00:07:25.378
There's no connection

00:07:25.378 --> 00:07:26.780
between the people of

00:07:26.780 --> 00:07:28.248
Greece and the politicians.

00:07:28.248 --> 00:07:30.317
We feel completely

00:07:30.317 --> 00:07:34.054
that no one...no one

00:07:34.054 --> 00:07:35.789
respects our wishes.

00:07:35.789 --> 00:07:38.258
The prices are going up...

00:07:38.258 --> 00:07:39.259
the salaries are going

00:07:39.259 --> 00:07:40.260
down...yeah...people have

00:07:40.260 --> 00:07:42.429
to cope ...with the situation.

00:07:42.429 --> 00:07:43.430
When I had my

00:07:43.430 --> 00:07:44.364
exams to get into the

00:07:44.364 --> 00:07:44.964
university, I was thinking

00:07:44.964 --> 00:07:47.934
that, "Wow! I'm going to

00:07:47.934 --> 00:07:48.935
become a pharmacist, I'm

00:07:48.935 --> 00:07:50.870
going to have a good job;

00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:52.839
I'm going to have a

00:07:52.839 --> 00:07:54.407
drugstore; I'm going to

00:07:54.407 --> 00:07:56.376
have a good life." And

00:07:56.376 --> 00:07:57.977
now...I just...I hope I

00:07:57.977 --> 00:08:01.047
get 30 Euros in 8 hours by

00:08:01.047 --> 00:08:04.150
becoming...by being a waitress.

00:08:04.150 --> 00:08:05.251
And I don't know

00:08:05.251 --> 00:08:05.819
what I will do.

00:08:05.819 --> 00:08:07.220
It's about 20 % of the people

00:08:07.220 --> 00:08:09.956
in...of the population

00:08:09.956 --> 00:08:10.957
lost their job during the

00:08:10.957 --> 00:08:12.726
last 5 years.

00:08:12.726 --> 00:08:14.094
20 % is unemployment.

00:08:14.094 --> 00:08:16.763
And that's why many people

00:08:16.763 --> 00:08:19.165
leave Greece...in order to

00:08:19.165 --> 00:08:22.302
find...to have a better future.

00:08:22.302 --> 00:08:22.969
Do you see young,

00:08:22.969 --> 00:08:24.170
talented people leaving

00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:25.472
Greece? I see it every

00:08:25.472 --> 00:08:26.806
day. People...colleagues

00:08:26.806 --> 00:08:27.807
here from my department

00:08:27.807 --> 00:08:28.842
have left for universities

00:08:28.842 --> 00:08:30.176
abroad- we're more likely

00:08:30.176 --> 00:08:32.045
to draw many high-quality

00:08:32.045 --> 00:08:33.580
people with very good

00:08:33.580 --> 00:08:35.115
qualifications here.

00:08:35.115 --> 00:08:36.316
And of course, those were

00:08:36.316 --> 00:08:38.318
easily hirable abroad.

00:08:40.987 --> 00:08:43.623
Stergios Sifnios runs an

00:08:43.623 --> 00:08:45.658
orphanage in Athens.

00:08:45.658 --> 00:08:47.327
The situation right now

00:08:47.327 --> 00:08:49.562
in Greece...it's very, very

00:08:49.562 --> 00:08:50.797
bad because the social

00:08:50.797 --> 00:08:52.298
services...the state

00:08:52.298 --> 00:08:53.933
social services are not

00:08:53.933 --> 00:08:54.601
working well. 

00:08:54.601 --> 00:08:55.402
It must have been...

00:08:55.402 --> 00:08:57.604
gone very far...

00:08:57.604 --> 00:08:58.972
a parent says that,

00:08:58.972 --> 00:09:00.907
"I'm so worried about

00:09:00.907 --> 00:09:03.576
my future; I can't keep my

00:09:03.576 --> 00:09:05.311
child in the family."

00:09:05.311 --> 00:09:06.780
Can you tell us about

00:09:06.780 --> 00:09:09.049
such an example?

00:09:09.049 --> 00:09:09.949
What motivates them?

00:09:09.949 --> 00:09:11.451
What do they say sometimes?

00:09:11.451 --> 00:09:12.452
You must understand that...a

00:09:12.452 --> 00:09:15.388
parent to come to ask us help,

00:09:15.388 --> 00:09:17.090
especially in Greece,

00:09:17.090 --> 00:09:20.727
where the ties in the family

00:09:20.727 --> 00:09:22.829
is...or was very strong,

00:09:22.829 --> 00:09:26.266
it is very strong...

00:09:26.266 --> 00:09:27.033
So you can

00:09:27.033 --> 00:09:29.636
imagine if a parent come

00:09:29.636 --> 00:09:31.137
to us, to ask for us help-

00:09:31.137 --> 00:09:32.138
it means that you

00:09:32.138 --> 00:09:33.206
really...the problem is

00:09:33.206 --> 00:09:35.208
very deep.

00:09:38.912 --> 00:09:40.280
I'm frustrated and most extremely

00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:42.315
worried by the turn things

00:09:42.315 --> 00:09:44.217
are taking, by the rise of

00:09:44.217 --> 00:09:45.752
population; by the rise of

00:09:45.752 --> 00:09:48.755
French parties who are

00:09:48.755 --> 00:09:51.124
promising empty words.

00:09:51.124 --> 00:09:53.460
Gabriel Sakellaridis is

00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:54.461
one of the leading

00:09:54.461 --> 00:09:55.728
economists of the new

00:09:55.728 --> 00:09:59.799
popular leftist party: Syriza.

00:09:59.799 --> 00:10:00.834
Right now we have

00:10:00.834 --> 00:10:01.935
a situation that is

00:10:01.935 --> 00:10:04.003
impossible, in my point of

00:10:04.003 --> 00:10:05.004
view, to have all this

00:10:05.004 --> 00:10:08.174
debt burden repaid. 	

00:10:08.174 --> 00:10:09.175
But you don't object to the

00:10:09.175 --> 00:10:11.177
bailout money going to

00:10:11.177 --> 00:10:13.680
Greece; you object to the

00:10:13.680 --> 00:10:15.014
conditions that you get

00:10:15.014 --> 00:10:17.016
those loans on?

00:10:17.016 --> 00:10:20.920
Yes. I mean for us...what we

00:10:20.920 --> 00:10:23.957
want to say is that right now-

00:10:23.957 --> 00:10:26.159
the money that we receive

00:10:26.159 --> 00:10:29.596
only go in order to repay

00:10:29.596 --> 00:10:32.599
our debt. I think Euro

00:10:32.599 --> 00:10:35.101
zone is going to break up

00:10:35.101 --> 00:10:37.103
under these policies,

00:10:37.103 --> 00:10:38.104
because they are not only

00:10:38.104 --> 00:10:39.105
implemented to Greece-

00:10:39.105 --> 00:10:40.540
they are implemented to

00:10:40.540 --> 00:10:41.975
other countries as well,

00:10:41.975 --> 00:10:43.977
such as Portugal, Italy,

00:10:43.977 --> 00:10:44.978
Spain, Ireland. And you

00:10:44.978 --> 00:10:46.980
see the situation in this

00:10:46.980 --> 00:10:48.982
country after some months

00:10:48.982 --> 00:10:49.949
of the implementation of

00:10:49.949 --> 00:10:50.950
these policies. The

00:10:50.950 --> 00:10:52.051
situation is getting worse

00:10:52.051 --> 00:10:53.052
and worse.

00:10:53.052 --> 00:10:54.053
Are you worried?

00:10:54.053 --> 00:10:56.756
I am extremely worried.

00:10:56.756 --> 00:10:59.058
But I want to believe

00:10:59.058 --> 00:11:01.995
that if I work hard...

00:11:01.995 --> 00:11:03.997
things are going better.

00:11:07.467 --> 00:11:09.869
I think that Greece shows

00:11:09.869 --> 00:11:12.005
that when you...

00:11:12.005 --> 00:11:13.873
ignore economic realities,

00:11:13.873 --> 00:11:15.975
and you build a...

00:11:15.975 --> 00:11:18.511
political project on

00:11:18.511 --> 00:11:21.014
basically sand, there are

00:11:21.014 --> 00:11:22.982
huge dangers to those

00:11:22.982 --> 00:11:23.983
ideals that you want to

00:11:23.983 --> 00:11:24.984
safeguard. And that

00:11:24.984 --> 00:11:27.987
affects the average Greek,

00:11:28.021 --> 00:11:29.556
whose future is being eroded.

00:11:29.556 --> 00:11:31.291
The problem in Greece

00:11:31.291 --> 00:11:32.292
is that Greece was

00:11:32.292 --> 00:11:33.293
allowed to be a free rider,

00:11:33.293 --> 00:11:36.496
so it came in on an

00:11:36.496 --> 00:11:37.497
illegitimate basis.

00:11:37.497 --> 00:11:38.498
But people thought that...

00:11:38.498 --> 00:11:39.499
Then that's a political decision!

00:11:39.499 --> 00:11:40.500
Well...it is and it isn't,

00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:41.601
in the sense that

00:11:41.601 --> 00:11:43.036
it's a political decision

00:11:43.036 --> 00:11:44.037
not just made by the Greeks,

00:11:44.037 --> 00:11:45.038
but made by everybody

00:11:45.038 --> 00:11:46.039
else as well.

00:11:46.039 --> 00:11:47.874
Yes, exactly, at the European level.

00:11:49.709 --> 00:11:51.844
The word austerity is now giving

00:11:51.844 --> 00:11:52.845
the creeps to pretty much

00:11:52.845 --> 00:11:54.047
all of Europe, but notably

00:11:54.047 --> 00:11:56.049
in Greece, because nobody

00:11:56.049 --> 00:11:58.551
wants to see that their

00:11:58.551 --> 00:11:59.552
standard of living

00:11:59.552 --> 00:12:02.155
forcedly going down

00:12:02.155 --> 00:12:03.156
because of the government,

00:12:03.156 --> 00:12:05.224
because of the mistakes

00:12:05.224 --> 00:12:06.092
that the government made.

00:12:06.092 --> 00:12:07.994
Do you think that this

00:12:07.994 --> 00:12:09.128
is a way out?

00:12:09.128 --> 00:12:11.130
It is! I mean...living

00:12:11.130 --> 00:12:13.066
beyond your means you know...

00:12:13.066 --> 00:12:14.334
stops at some point; you can't do

00:12:14.334 --> 00:12:17.070
it forever. Also you can't

00:12:17.070 --> 00:12:18.504
spend other people's money

00:12:18.504 --> 00:12:20.573
forever, and politicians

00:12:20.573 --> 00:12:21.674
have been doing that, and

00:12:21.674 --> 00:12:22.308
I understand that Greeks

00:12:22.308 --> 00:12:23.476
have been living beyond

00:12:23.476 --> 00:12:24.477
their means for a long

00:12:24.477 --> 00:12:27.013
time, but they will have

00:12:27.013 --> 00:12:29.849
to change that, especially

00:12:29.849 --> 00:12:30.650
people in the public

00:12:30.650 --> 00:12:31.451
sector. They will have to

00:12:31.451 --> 00:12:33.086
take the responsibility

00:12:33.086 --> 00:12:36.022
of...you know...

00:12:36.022 --> 00:12:37.957
dealing with the situation.

00:12:37.957 --> 00:12:40.393
People of the public sector, you said?

00:12:40.393 --> 00:12:42.128
Yes! Yes.

00:12:42.128 --> 00:12:43.663
Now, say you take an

00:12:43.663 --> 00:12:46.032
average worker of this

00:12:46.032 --> 00:12:49.035
public sector in Greece...

00:12:49.035 --> 00:12:50.570
a teacher, for example.

00:12:50.570 --> 00:12:52.705
How is she, or he held responsible

00:12:52.705 --> 00:12:54.774
for what's going on in the country?

00:12:54.774 --> 00:12:55.842
When government

00:12:55.842 --> 00:12:57.210
runs out of money, then

00:12:57.210 --> 00:12:58.511
it's obvious that you will

00:12:58.511 --> 00:13:00.346
lose your job.

00:13:00.346 --> 00:13:04.651
So I don't, ..see any reason

00:13:04.651 --> 00:13:05.551
of these people saying,

00:13:05.551 --> 00:13:08.554
"Oh, we have these jobs...

00:13:08.554 --> 00:13:09.656
we need to keep them.

00:13:09.656 --> 00:13:10.657
We haven't done

00:13:10.657 --> 00:13:11.658
anything wrong." Now...if

00:13:11.658 --> 00:13:12.659
If I had to pinpoint one

00:13:12.659 --> 00:13:13.826
responsible for what's

00:13:13.826 --> 00:13:16.129
going on, in Greece,

00:13:16.129 --> 00:13:17.130
in Europe just in general,

00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:18.131
it would be the financial

00:13:18.131 --> 00:13:21.668
sector. It would be the

00:13:21.668 --> 00:13:23.670
urge, the greed- that's

00:13:23.670 --> 00:13:24.671
driving people to look for

00:13:24.671 --> 00:13:25.738
more profits. That's why

00:13:25.738 --> 00:13:26.973
so much money has been

00:13:26.973 --> 00:13:28.341
invested in bonds...

00:13:28.341 --> 00:13:30.143
in Greek bonds, for example,

00:13:30.143 --> 00:13:31.477
because they were

00:13:31.477 --> 00:13:32.812
promising a higher yield.

00:13:32.812 --> 00:13:34.280
Everyone is self-interested.

00:13:34.280 --> 00:13:35.515
It's not just banking sector,

00:13:35.515 --> 00:13:37.317
it's you and I.

00:13:37.317 --> 00:13:39.018
We have...we are self-interested;

00:13:39.018 --> 00:13:40.019
so we act based on

00:13:40.019 --> 00:13:42.021
self-interest.

00:13:42.021 --> 00:13:44.023
So...banking sector is not

00:13:44.023 --> 00:13:47.226
an exception. Second thing

00:13:47.226 --> 00:13:49.796
related to that...no one

00:13:49.796 --> 00:13:52.298
is too big to fail, even banks.

00:13:52.298 --> 00:13:53.333
You know...if they

00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:54.500
make mistakes they should

00:13:54.500 --> 00:13:56.703
take responsibility for that.

00:13:56.703 --> 00:13:58.237
And I think it is

00:13:58.237 --> 00:13:59.572
government that is saying,

00:13:59.572 --> 00:14:00.106
"Oh we have to save this

00:14:00.106 --> 00:14:01.974
bank, or we have to save

00:14:01.974 --> 00:14:03.776
this company, we have to

00:14:03.776 --> 00:14:04.310
save these people

00:14:04.310 --> 00:14:05.712
just because it's going to

00:14:05.712 --> 00:14:08.581
have you know, domino effect

00:14:08.581 --> 00:14:09.849
the rest of the economy.

00:14:09.849 --> 00:14:10.983
I think that's a mistake.

00:14:10.983 --> 00:14:12.618
Brussels is responsible

00:14:12.618 --> 00:14:13.820
for gathering together

00:14:13.820 --> 00:14:16.355
many different countries

00:14:16.355 --> 00:14:17.390
of different level,

00:14:17.390 --> 00:14:19.492
of different GDP size,

00:14:19.492 --> 00:14:20.159
for example.

00:14:20.159 --> 00:14:21.327
Greece just accounts for

00:14:21.327 --> 00:14:23.329
6% of the EU's GDP.

00:14:23.329 --> 00:14:25.698
But altogether, it's their

00:14:25.698 --> 00:14:27.266
fault basically that this

00:14:27.266 --> 00:14:28.267
union was founded with a

00:14:28.267 --> 00:14:31.070
common currency which is

00:14:31.070 --> 00:14:33.072
tying it up so closely

00:14:33.072 --> 00:14:35.108
together. But with a

00:14:35.108 --> 00:14:35.575
different budget, with

00:14:35.575 --> 00:14:37.710
non-coordinated non-

00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:38.678
harmonized budget and

00:14:38.678 --> 00:14:40.980
fiscal policies, and that

00:14:40.980 --> 00:14:41.981
appears to be a way out.

00:14:41.981 --> 00:14:44.016
I mean, if the EU had a

00:14:44.016 --> 00:14:45.017
balanced fiscal policy,

00:14:45.017 --> 00:14:47.086
as in the taxes would be

00:14:47.086 --> 00:14:48.287
pretty much the same level

00:14:48.287 --> 00:14:49.288
everywhere, that would

00:14:49.288 --> 00:14:51.524
create a homogenous labor

00:14:51.524 --> 00:14:53.459
market, for example, in the EU.

00:14:53.459 --> 00:14:54.927
Well, I agree that,

00:14:54.927 --> 00:14:56.562
you know, that would be a

00:14:56.562 --> 00:14:57.897
solution to have more

00:14:57.897 --> 00:14:59.031
stable Europe. But I don't

00:14:59.031 --> 00:14:59.966
think that's good for the

00:14:59.966 --> 00:15:01.834
economies of Europe.

00:15:01.834 --> 00:15:02.835
I think it's better to have

00:15:02.835 --> 00:15:03.703
the position among them in

00:15:03.703 --> 00:15:05.705
terms of the currencies

00:15:05.705 --> 00:15:07.573
they have, in terms of

00:15:07.573 --> 00:15:10.710
their fiscal policies, in

00:15:10.710 --> 00:15:11.711
terms of the taxation.

00:15:11.711 --> 00:15:14.847
So I would actually argue

00:15:14.847 --> 00:15:15.848
that we should go back

00:15:15.848 --> 00:15:18.451
and abolish the Euro or have

00:15:18.451 --> 00:15:19.452
even like, you know,

00:15:19.452 --> 00:15:21.254
various Euro areas. 		

00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:22.989
But you know, you have to

00:15:22.989 --> 00:15:25.525
remember that Europe has

00:15:25.525 --> 00:15:28.060
not been the same every

00:15:28.060 --> 00:15:30.430
5, 10 years. I started living

00:15:30.430 --> 00:15:32.498
there when it was only

00:15:32.498 --> 00:15:34.000
12 countries. I left it when

00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:35.568
it was 15 countries...

00:15:35.568 --> 00:15:37.603
now it's 27 in the EU.

00:15:37.603 --> 00:15:40.573
And they had political goal,

00:15:40.573 --> 00:15:44.177
disregarding the economics.

00:15:44.177 --> 00:15:45.278
And that is

00:15:45.278 --> 00:15:46.212
haunting them, and the

00:15:46.212 --> 00:15:49.048
sooner they face the truth,

00:15:49.048 --> 00:15:50.750
the sooner we will

00:15:50.750 --> 00:15:53.452
be able to get out of the crisis.

00:15:53.452 --> 00:15:54.453
So really...the only

00:15:54.453 --> 00:15:55.454
certain thing about

00:15:55.454 --> 00:15:56.389
this situation is its

00:15:56.389 --> 00:15:57.590
complete uncertainty,

00:15:57.590 --> 00:15:58.224
wouldn't you say?

00:15:58.224 --> 00:15:59.959
Yeah. I would agree. 		

00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:01.727
Hey, you mentioned political

00:16:01.727 --> 00:16:03.462
leadership, and that's

00:16:03.462 --> 00:16:05.064
exactly what we looked at

00:16:05.064 --> 00:16:06.065
with the film crew in

00:16:06.065 --> 00:16:07.066
Brussels; the fact that

00:16:07.066 --> 00:16:07.967
they knew that they were

00:16:07.967 --> 00:16:08.968
going to have problems

00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:11.804
with debts, with deficits

00:16:11.804 --> 00:16:12.805
and easy money.

00:16:12.805 --> 00:16:13.906
So they built these rules

00:16:13.906 --> 00:16:14.907
and institutions to deal with it,

00:16:14.907 --> 00:16:16.275
but the problem was

00:16:16.275 --> 00:16:17.743
that in the end, no one

00:16:17.743 --> 00:16:19.545
cared about them.

00:16:19.812 --> 00:16:21.581
It's a sorry tale,

00:16:21.581 --> 00:16:23.082
it's a sorry tale.

00:16:24.917 --> 00:16:25.918
It could have been

00:16:25.918 --> 00:16:27.854
done so much better with

00:16:27.854 --> 00:16:29.989
a little bit of courage a civile,

00:16:29.989 --> 00:16:31.757
or "civil courage,"

00:16:31.757 --> 00:16:33.259
if you like.

00:16:34.994 --> 00:16:36.295
When the sovereign debt

00:16:36.295 --> 00:16:37.530
crisis exploded, the

00:16:37.530 --> 00:16:38.998
people of Europe looked to

00:16:38.998 --> 00:16:39.999
Brussels, the home of the

00:16:39.999 --> 00:16:41.334
political elite.

00:16:41.334 --> 00:16:43.135
This was their opportunity

00:16:43.135 --> 00:16:47.006
to show what they are made of.

00:16:47.006 --> 00:16:49.408
In 2002, the EU said it had

00:16:49.408 --> 00:16:51.878
strict rules on debts and deficits.

00:16:51.878 --> 00:16:54.947
In 2003, they broke those rules.

00:16:54.947 --> 00:16:55.948
But there was one thing it

00:16:55.948 --> 00:16:57.183
would never do...bail out

00:16:57.183 --> 00:16:58.184
a country that had

00:16:58.184 --> 00:16:59.318
borrowed too much.

00:16:59.318 --> 00:17:00.987
In 2010 they did.

00:17:00.987 --> 00:17:02.488
But there was one thing

00:17:02.488 --> 00:17:03.489
that they would never do:

00:17:03.489 --> 00:17:04.323
They would never buy

00:17:04.323 --> 00:17:06.325
government bonds from countries

00:17:06.325 --> 00:17:07.326
that had borrowed too much.

00:17:07.326 --> 00:17:10.663
Just the next week they did.

00:17:10.663 --> 00:17:11.931
Now they say they have new

00:17:11.931 --> 00:17:14.033
strict rules on debts and

00:17:14.033 --> 00:17:15.868
deficits. The question is:

00:17:15.868 --> 00:17:17.670
Will they stand by their

00:17:17.670 --> 00:17:18.838
words this time?

00:17:19.972 --> 00:17:21.974
This is Fritz Bolkestein.

00:17:21.974 --> 00:17:23.509
As a former member of the

00:17:23.509 --> 00:17:24.510
European Commission,

00:17:24.510 --> 00:17:26.779
he has experience from the

00:17:26.779 --> 00:17:28.247
top level of European

00:17:28.247 --> 00:17:30.983
politics. Why does this

00:17:30.983 --> 00:17:31.984
happen again and again?

00:17:31.984 --> 00:17:33.786
They said that we had the

00:17:33.786 --> 00:17:34.787
Stability Pact and then

00:17:34.787 --> 00:17:35.788
they broke the rules and

00:17:35.788 --> 00:17:36.989
nothing happened, they

00:17:36.989 --> 00:17:37.990
said that they wouldn't

00:17:37.990 --> 00:17:39.091
bail out any particular

00:17:39.091 --> 00:17:40.092
country, but then they

00:17:40.092 --> 00:17:40.993
bailed out Greece.

00:17:40.993 --> 00:17:42.962
Every rule has been broken,

00:17:42.962 --> 00:17:44.630
every rule has been broken;

00:17:44.630 --> 00:17:48.734
every remedy that now is

00:17:48.734 --> 00:17:51.003
proposed...infringes the

00:17:51.003 --> 00:17:52.805
original treaty.

00:17:56.976 --> 00:17:59.045
What was the discussion like in the

00:17:59.045 --> 00:18:00.913
Commission when the rules

00:18:00.913 --> 00:18:01.447
were broken?

00:18:01.447 --> 00:18:04.784
Very little, very little, very little.

00:18:04.784 --> 00:18:06.285
Is it fair to say that

00:18:06.285 --> 00:18:08.120
a lot of people in

00:18:08.120 --> 00:18:09.689
influential positions knew

00:18:09.689 --> 00:18:11.190
that there were problems?

00:18:11.190 --> 00:18:12.191
Yeah. Early on? Yeah.

00:18:12.191 --> 00:18:13.893
But they didn't really have

00:18:13.893 --> 00:18:15.261
the guts to do something about it.

00:18:15.261 --> 00:18:16.696
That is true, I afraid that

00:18:16.696 --> 00:18:17.697
is true...because the

00:18:17.697 --> 00:18:18.698
situation in Greece, and

00:18:18.698 --> 00:18:19.699
also in Italy was known-

00:18:19.699 --> 00:18:21.701
but not acted upon.

00:18:23.869 --> 00:18:25.871
I think the European Union

00:18:25.871 --> 00:18:27.006
is a marvelous thing,

00:18:27.006 --> 00:18:30.943
if only because it's kept the peace.

00:18:30.943 --> 00:18:32.278
I was born in 1933,

00:18:32.278 --> 00:18:33.512
so I know what I'm talking about.

00:18:33.512 --> 00:18:36.415
And that is now the

00:18:36.415 --> 00:18:37.216
normal situation.

00:18:37.216 --> 00:18:39.385
It has never been the case,

00:18:39.385 --> 00:18:40.586
now it is the case.

00:18:40.586 --> 00:18:42.622
So I am a supporter of the

00:18:42.622 --> 00:18:43.623
European Union, but what

00:18:43.623 --> 00:18:44.924
we needed was a little bit more

00:18:44.924 --> 00:18:46.625
common sense, and a

00:18:46.625 --> 00:18:49.195
little bit more of guts.

00:18:49.195 --> 00:18:50.496
Then I think we would not

00:18:50.496 --> 00:18:53.332
be in the pickle that we are now in.

00:18:57.970 --> 00:18:59.372
Isn't there a lack of

00:18:59.372 --> 00:19:00.606
credibility right now for

00:19:00.606 --> 00:19:01.140
the Commission?

00:19:01.140 --> 00:19:02.942
It began with a fiscal pact

00:19:02.942 --> 00:19:04.744
on debts and deficits,

00:19:04.744 --> 00:19:06.545
and just one year later

00:19:06.545 --> 00:19:08.547
several countries broke

00:19:08.547 --> 00:19:09.215
those rules. But at least

00:19:09.215 --> 00:19:11.250
you would never bail out

00:19:11.250 --> 00:19:13.285
countries that broke the rules.

00:19:13.285 --> 00:19:15.287
And in 2010 you did-

00:19:15.287 --> 00:19:16.288
but at least you wouldn't

00:19:16.288 --> 00:19:17.556
buy their sovereign government

00:19:17.556 --> 00:19:18.791
bonds, but then you did.

00:19:18.791 --> 00:19:20.026
And now we have this new

00:19:20.026 --> 00:19:21.794
fiscal pact, and you have

00:19:21.794 --> 00:19:23.696
new targets for Spain's

00:19:23.696 --> 00:19:24.930
deficit and you have

00:19:24.930 --> 00:19:27.333
already renegotiated that...

00:19:27.333 --> 00:19:28.267
that deficit rule.

00:19:28.267 --> 00:19:29.802
So the question is: Why should

00:19:29.802 --> 00:19:32.672
we take your word for granted

00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:34.140
this time?

00:19:34.140 --> 00:19:36.375
It's very important to

00:19:36.375 --> 00:19:38.377
differentiate very clearly, the

00:19:38.377 --> 00:19:39.178
political decisions which

00:19:39.178 --> 00:19:40.880
are based on statistics,

00:19:40.880 --> 00:19:44.950
and statistics itself.

00:19:44.950 --> 00:19:48.020
And I think that in cases

00:19:48.020 --> 00:19:49.221
which you mentioned

00:19:49.221 --> 00:19:52.892
statistics was published

00:19:52.892 --> 00:19:54.827
correctly, of course with

00:19:54.827 --> 00:19:56.762
that problem was Greek

00:19:56.762 --> 00:19:59.799
deficit figures for 2009,

00:19:59.799 --> 00:20:02.968
and actually our experts

00:20:02.968 --> 00:20:06.272
helped to solve these

00:20:06.272 --> 00:20:07.873
problems. By letting Italy

00:20:07.873 --> 00:20:10.109
in when it was not

00:20:10.109 --> 00:20:11.010
satisfying the criteria,

00:20:11.010 --> 00:20:14.413
they could later not very

00:20:14.413 --> 00:20:15.648
well refuse Greece.

00:20:15.648 --> 00:20:18.150
That is the true reason why

00:20:18.150 --> 00:20:20.352
Greece was let in-

00:20:20.352 --> 00:20:21.587
not because they falsified

00:20:21.587 --> 00:20:22.588
their statistics, which

00:20:22.588 --> 00:20:23.589
they did of course,

00:20:23.589 --> 00:20:26.125
but because the European

00:20:26.125 --> 00:20:27.126
Council- which is the heads

00:20:27.126 --> 00:20:29.328
of states and governments,

00:20:29.328 --> 00:20:30.329
thought that they

00:20:30.329 --> 00:20:31.330
could not refuse

00:20:31.330 --> 00:20:32.031
Greece what they had

00:20:32.031 --> 00:20:33.032
allowed Italy, so there

00:20:33.032 --> 00:20:34.934
you have the curse of the

00:20:34.934 --> 00:20:38.204
evil deed. So, it means

00:20:38.204 --> 00:20:41.173
that statistics already

00:20:41.173 --> 00:20:44.009
produces a good quality

00:20:44.009 --> 00:20:45.044
basis for sound decision

00:20:45.044 --> 00:20:47.046
making, but what we wanted

00:20:47.046 --> 00:20:51.917
to do to go further and to

00:20:51.917 --> 00:20:54.320
ensure that never in the

00:20:54.320 --> 00:20:57.289
future we will have,

00:20:57.289 --> 00:20:58.290
you know, any political

00:20:58.290 --> 00:20:59.458
interference into

00:20:59.458 --> 00:21:03.562
statistics- and this is what

00:21:03.562 --> 00:21:06.999
we proposed was our regulation.

00:21:06.999 --> 00:21:08.000
This lack of guts among

00:21:08.000 --> 00:21:09.935
politicians...what's the

00:21:09.935 --> 00:21:11.003
reason for this? What part

00:21:11.003 --> 00:21:12.738
of human nature explains

00:21:12.738 --> 00:21:14.406
this? Well, (laughter)

00:21:14.406 --> 00:21:16.342
that's a big question.

00:21:16.342 --> 00:21:17.510
I'm not really used to talking

00:21:17.510 --> 00:21:19.111
about human nature.

00:21:19.111 --> 00:21:21.947
But what I do know is that

00:21:21.947 --> 00:21:25.017
not many people like

00:21:25.017 --> 00:21:29.555
standing alone...

00:21:31.390 --> 00:21:36.395
most go with the herd...

00:21:36.395 --> 00:21:37.463
although people who stand alone

00:21:37.463 --> 00:21:40.466
are not necessarily incorrect.

00:21:52.845 --> 00:21:53.846
What do you think is the

00:21:53.846 --> 00:21:54.847
underlying cause of the crisis?

00:21:54.847 --> 00:21:55.848
I gather you think

00:21:55.848 --> 00:21:56.849
it's something more than

00:21:56.849 --> 00:21:58.717
just purely financial matters.

00:21:58.717 --> 00:21:59.718
The origins of this crisis

00:21:59.718 --> 00:22:00.986
lie, in my view,

00:22:00.986 --> 00:22:02.054
in the development of

00:22:02.054 --> 00:22:03.589
a kind of a win-lose capitalism.

00:22:03.589 --> 00:22:04.657
Too few people win,

00:22:04.657 --> 00:22:06.325
everybody else loses.

00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:07.326
And I think this is most

00:22:07.326 --> 00:22:08.327
obvious in the world of

00:22:08.327 --> 00:22:09.828
ordinary people, most

00:22:09.828 --> 00:22:11.497
people rely on wages.

00:22:11.497 --> 00:22:12.131
Wages have been falling

00:22:12.131 --> 00:22:14.767
relative to GDP growth

00:22:14.767 --> 00:22:16.836
since 1968, so people

00:22:16.836 --> 00:22:18.837
think labor has been

00:22:18.837 --> 00:22:19.839
earning less and less.

00:22:19.839 --> 00:22:20.839
And they've made up the

00:22:20.839 --> 00:22:21.574
difference with debt.

00:22:21.574 --> 00:22:23.642
I think you're partly correct,

00:22:23.642 --> 00:22:25.244
but I'm not quite as

00:22:25.244 --> 00:22:26.245
pessimistic as you.

00:22:26.245 --> 00:22:28.147
In fact, in the U.S.

00:22:28.147 --> 00:22:30.149
wages have not declined...

00:22:30.149 --> 00:22:31.150
that's a myth. What's happened

00:22:31.150 --> 00:22:33.018
in the last ten years is the

00:22:33.018 --> 00:22:34.153
Federal Reserve has

00:22:34.153 --> 00:22:35.354
increased the money supply

00:22:35.354 --> 00:22:36.422
too much.

00:22:36.422 --> 00:22:38.290
Government officials have tried

00:22:38.290 --> 00:22:39.291
to increase artificially the

00:22:39.291 --> 00:22:40.292
supply of home ownership.

00:22:40.292 --> 00:22:41.694
I think it's these more

00:22:41.694 --> 00:22:43.229
economic factors that

00:22:43.229 --> 00:22:45.197
drove this bubble and then

00:22:45.197 --> 00:22:46.031
that bubble was inevitably

00:22:46.031 --> 00:22:48.100
destined to burst, and it did.

00:22:48.100 --> 00:22:49.702
We agree that you

00:22:49.702 --> 00:22:50.703
know that the culture

00:22:50.703 --> 00:22:51.704
should be improved.

00:22:51.704 --> 00:22:52.838
I'm in favor of less crony

00:22:52.838 --> 00:22:53.839
capitalism, less influence

00:22:53.839 --> 00:22:55.641
to special interest groups.

00:22:55.641 --> 00:22:56.642
We both agree that

00:22:56.642 --> 00:22:58.043
those matter; but I don't

00:22:58.043 --> 00:22:59.044
think that the culture of

00:22:59.044 --> 00:23:00.512
capitalism has become so

00:23:00.512 --> 00:23:03.015
decrepit, and so bad that

00:23:03.015 --> 00:23:05.217
fundamental change on that

00:23:05.217 --> 00:23:06.218
front is required.

00:23:06.218 --> 00:23:08.053
I think the real problem

00:23:08.053 --> 00:23:09.355
lies with the state,

00:23:09.355 --> 00:23:11.290
lies with the state's efforts

00:23:11.290 --> 00:23:12.658
to prop up its cronies.

00:23:12.658 --> 00:23:14.660
Actually, just to put it very

00:23:14.660 --> 00:23:16.895
simply, successful capitalists

00:23:16.895 --> 00:23:17.896
hate capitalism.

00:23:17.896 --> 00:23:18.897
And what they do

00:23:18.897 --> 00:23:20.599
is they conspire often

00:23:20.599 --> 00:23:21.600
with each other. And this

00:23:21.600 --> 00:23:22.735
is what all legal cases in

00:23:22.735 --> 00:23:23.769
competition are about.

00:23:23.769 --> 00:23:24.770
They're not about the

00:23:24.770 --> 00:23:25.771
government, they're about

00:23:25.771 --> 00:23:26.972
cartels forming,

00:23:26.972 --> 00:23:28.240
oligopolies forming,

00:23:28.240 --> 00:23:29.241
that essentially say to small

00:23:29.241 --> 00:23:31.010
businesses to people who

00:23:31.010 --> 00:23:32.011
want to break in - no you

00:23:32.011 --> 00:23:33.012
can't, we're gonna buy you

00:23:33.012 --> 00:23:34.013
out, we're gonna stop you,

00:23:34.013 --> 00:23:35.047
we're gonna create

00:23:35.047 --> 00:23:36.048
barriers to market entry.

00:23:36.048 --> 00:23:37.082
If you were a real free

00:23:37.082 --> 00:23:38.617
marketer I'd suggest yes

00:23:38.617 --> 00:23:40.019
have that critique of the

00:23:40.019 --> 00:23:41.153
state, agree with it...

00:23:41.153 --> 00:23:42.221
but for goodness sake-

00:23:42.221 --> 00:23:43.222
look at the history,

00:23:43.222 --> 00:23:44.590
look at the reality.

00:23:44.590 --> 00:23:45.591
Let's also have a critique of the

00:23:45.591 --> 00:23:46.592
private sector. I have

00:23:46.592 --> 00:23:47.593
looked at the reality.

00:23:47.593 --> 00:23:48.460
I've actually researched

00:23:48.460 --> 00:23:49.461
this in great detail.

00:23:49.461 --> 00:23:51.330
And in the U.S. the history

00:23:51.330 --> 00:23:53.565
is monopolies are almost

00:23:53.565 --> 00:23:54.066
always a product of the

00:23:54.066 --> 00:23:55.200
government and the

00:23:55.200 --> 00:23:57.036
anti-trust laws, it's

00:23:57.036 --> 00:23:58.037
called in the U.S., is

00:23:58.037 --> 00:23:59.939
used mostly to suppress

00:23:59.939 --> 00:24:00.873
competition, not to

00:24:00.873 --> 00:24:02.541
promote competition.

00:24:02.541 --> 00:24:04.810
Name me one private sector

00:24:04.810 --> 00:24:06.478
monopoly that has lasted

00:24:06.478 --> 00:24:07.713
on its own consumers- that

00:24:07.713 --> 00:24:08.714
did not have any support

00:24:08.714 --> 00:24:09.715
from the state.

00:24:09.715 --> 00:24:10.716
Well, I think you can look

00:24:10.716 --> 00:24:11.717
at what's happened in food

00:24:11.717 --> 00:24:12.918
retail. I think you can

00:24:12.918 --> 00:24:13.919
look at what's happened in

00:24:13.919 --> 00:24:15.521
finance and auditing and

00:24:15.521 --> 00:24:18.157
almost any large business

00:24:18.157 --> 00:24:19.992
sector, what you see over

00:24:19.992 --> 00:24:20.993
time is a conspiracy

00:24:20.993 --> 00:24:22.194
against competition by the

00:24:22.194 --> 00:24:23.996
dominant players in that market.

00:24:23.996 --> 00:24:24.997
Reality of the

00:24:24.997 --> 00:24:26.031
situation is if you want

00:24:26.031 --> 00:24:27.166
to start a business,

00:24:27.166 --> 00:24:29.301
if you want to become

00:24:29.301 --> 00:24:30.302
independent, if you want

00:24:30.302 --> 00:24:32.137
to innovate now in both my

00:24:32.137 --> 00:24:33.138
county, United Kingdom and

00:24:33.138 --> 00:24:35.274
United States- economic

00:24:35.274 --> 00:24:36.275
power concentrates, they

00:24:36.275 --> 00:24:38.043
own too much and they

00:24:38.043 --> 00:24:38.811
won't let you in.

00:24:38.811 --> 00:24:39.678
How can you say that?

00:24:39.678 --> 00:24:42.014
Google just started in 1998;

00:24:42.014 --> 00:24:43.015
it's one of the most powerful

00:24:43.015 --> 00:24:44.016
companies in the world.

00:24:44.016 --> 00:24:45.017
The thing didn't even

00:24:45.017 --> 00:24:46.518
exist 15 years ago!

00:24:46.518 --> 00:24:47.519
But that's because it's a new

00:24:47.519 --> 00:24:48.520
technological development,

00:24:48.520 --> 00:24:49.421
in a new market area.

00:24:49.421 --> 00:24:50.422
But, that's... And now many

00:24:50.422 --> 00:24:51.423
people are worried about

00:24:51.423 --> 00:24:53.759
Google's monopoly power.

00:24:53.759 --> 00:24:54.860
And I would... And that

00:24:54.860 --> 00:24:55.861
exactly makes my point!

00:24:55.861 --> 00:24:56.895
And I would...no, no, no.

00:24:56.895 --> 00:24:57.997
I would bet them.

00:24:57.997 --> 00:24:59.965
Google is free. Google is free!

00:24:59.965 --> 00:25:02.568
How is anyone hurt by Google?

00:25:02.568 --> 00:25:04.336
It's expanded our horizons,

00:25:04.336 --> 00:25:05.070
our opportunities...as

00:25:05.070 --> 00:25:06.071
consumers and businessmen.

00:25:06.071 --> 00:25:07.573
Because you cannot as a

00:25:07.573 --> 00:25:08.574
small player, as a small

00:25:08.574 --> 00:25:09.575
business starter -

00:25:09.575 --> 00:25:12.077
you cannot - the Internet

00:25:12.077 --> 00:25:13.078
you know, the ideologues of

00:25:13.078 --> 00:25:14.079
the Internet used to say

00:25:14.079 --> 00:25:15.481
it's a great space where

00:25:15.481 --> 00:25:16.482
the small can come and

00:25:16.482 --> 00:25:17.616
compete together with the big,

00:25:17.616 --> 00:25:19.685
but the reality is the opposite.

00:25:19.685 --> 00:25:20.686
Look at how...

00:25:20.686 --> 00:25:20.819
...But that's

00:25:20.819 --> 00:25:22.154
because Google is efficient!

00:25:22.154 --> 00:25:23.422
No, it's not just because

00:25:23.422 --> 00:25:24.423
of market efficiency.

00:25:24.423 --> 00:25:24.990
I'm a great fan of Apple.

00:25:24.990 --> 00:25:26.291
I'm a great fan of Google.

00:25:26.291 --> 00:25:27.359
These are all good companies

00:25:27.359 --> 00:25:28.360
who do great things.

00:25:28.360 --> 00:25:29.995
But what they actually also do-

00:25:29.995 --> 00:25:30.996
is to create barriers to

00:25:30.996 --> 00:25:32.998
market entry, is create

00:25:32.998 --> 00:25:35.000
shut-outs, is to create

00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:36.001
forms that are, in effect,

00:25:36.001 --> 00:25:39.004
a form of monopoly power.

00:25:39.004 --> 00:25:40.005
Now what I find that is

00:25:40.005 --> 00:25:41.006
really disturbing is-

00:25:41.006 --> 00:25:43.008
that the modern right

00:25:43.008 --> 00:25:44.009
can't see this...it's

00:25:44.009 --> 00:25:45.010
blind to this. It's says,

00:25:45.010 --> 00:25:46.245
oh it's just a successful company,

00:25:46.245 --> 00:25:47.379
and there's no problem

00:25:47.379 --> 00:25:48.547
with a successful company.

00:25:48.547 --> 00:25:49.681
But nobody has

00:25:49.681 --> 00:25:50.816
thought this in economic

00:25:50.816 --> 00:25:51.984
thought for hundreds of

00:25:51.984 --> 00:25:53.986
years until Milton Friedman

00:25:53.986 --> 00:25:54.987
per versed at the

00:25:54.987 --> 00:25:55.687
teachings of Hayek.

00:25:55.687 --> 00:25:57.723
And I think what Friedman did,

00:25:57.723 --> 00:25:59.925
if I may go on, which I

00:25:59.925 --> 00:26:00.959
think is so worrying, is

00:26:00.959 --> 00:26:01.960
he said we are going to

00:26:01.960 --> 00:26:02.961
have competition law based

00:26:02.961 --> 00:26:04.930
just on consumer welfare.

00:26:04.930 --> 00:26:06.632
And consumer welfare,

00:26:06.632 --> 00:26:07.633
which kind of sounds weird,

00:26:07.633 --> 00:26:08.634
what does that mean?

00:26:08.634 --> 00:26:09.802
It means low prices.

00:26:09.802 --> 00:26:10.803
The only model that we

00:26:10.803 --> 00:26:11.804
need is low prices,

00:26:11.804 --> 00:26:12.805
because if we have low

00:26:12.805 --> 00:26:15.073
prices as the model for

00:26:15.073 --> 00:26:16.074
competition, monopolies

00:26:16.074 --> 00:26:17.309
can't deliver you low

00:26:17.309 --> 00:26:18.410
prices and they will break.

00:26:18.410 --> 00:26:19.478
I disagree with you.

00:26:19.478 --> 00:26:20.579
I think Friedman was right.

00:26:20.579 --> 00:26:21.079
If you look at the history

00:26:21.079 --> 00:26:22.214
when government

00:26:22.214 --> 00:26:23.215
has stayed out, yes

00:26:23.215 --> 00:26:24.616
you have the large firms.

00:26:24.616 --> 00:26:26.418
It's very difficult for

00:26:26.418 --> 00:26:27.419
inefficient firms to

00:26:27.419 --> 00:26:28.987
compete with their larger

00:26:28.987 --> 00:26:30.522
rivals- but consumers

00:26:30.522 --> 00:26:32.057
benefit. The history of

00:26:32.057 --> 00:26:34.293
capitalism in America and

00:26:34.293 --> 00:26:37.696
in Europe tells me that

00:26:37.696 --> 00:26:39.398
competition is very dynamic.

00:26:39.398 --> 00:26:40.332
The only way it can

00:26:40.332 --> 00:26:41.166
be suppressed for any

00:26:41.166 --> 00:26:42.801
length of time is when it

00:26:42.801 --> 00:26:43.802
gets government

00:26:43.802 --> 00:26:44.803
privileges. I think I fear

00:26:44.803 --> 00:26:46.538
this is ideology speaking,

00:26:46.538 --> 00:26:46.839
not truth.

00:26:46.839 --> 00:26:49.074
If you look at... I think

00:26:49.074 --> 00:26:50.909
it's facts speaking.

00:26:52.010 --> 00:26:53.312
I recently went to Greece and

00:26:53.312 --> 00:26:56.515
I've never seen that depth of

00:26:56.515 --> 00:26:57.716
fear for the future and

00:26:57.716 --> 00:26:59.818
hopelessness among people,

00:26:59.818 --> 00:27:02.354
combined with a rejection

00:27:02.354 --> 00:27:03.422
of the old political

00:27:03.422 --> 00:27:04.256
class...the sense of

00:27:04.256 --> 00:27:05.824
that they've been betrayed by

00:27:05.824 --> 00:27:07.459
politicians who promised

00:27:07.459 --> 00:27:09.595
them everything, and now

00:27:09.595 --> 00:27:10.596
we see the results of that.

00:27:10.596 --> 00:27:11.830
And my fear is that

00:27:11.830 --> 00:27:13.866
this is just the beginning-

00:27:13.866 --> 00:27:14.833
that this might happen

00:27:14.833 --> 00:27:16.368
to other European

00:27:16.368 --> 00:27:17.369
countries as well.

00:27:17.369 --> 00:27:19.538
I'm coming from France Paris,

00:27:19.538 --> 00:27:22.107
and I observe some similar

00:27:22.107 --> 00:27:25.344
symptoms. I mean, public

00:27:25.344 --> 00:27:26.712
finances, the way of

00:27:26.712 --> 00:27:30.983
conducting public policy.

00:27:30.983 --> 00:27:33.285
And French are very afraid

00:27:33.285 --> 00:27:35.120
of what happens with Greece.

00:27:35.120 --> 00:27:37.256
My question when I look

00:27:37.256 --> 00:27:39.191
at France and other countries

00:27:39.191 --> 00:27:41.426
is that: we always

00:27:41.426 --> 00:27:42.327
seem to get new politicians

00:27:42.327 --> 00:27:43.896
to say that,

00:27:43.896 --> 00:27:45.664
"Look we have an easier

00:27:45.664 --> 00:27:46.698
way of fixing the problems.

00:27:46.698 --> 00:27:48.567
We can somehow

00:27:48.567 --> 00:27:51.270
find the money, or the

00:27:51.270 --> 00:27:52.971
kind of ways of raising

00:27:52.971 --> 00:27:55.207
new loans that will make

00:27:55.207 --> 00:27:56.508
the transition easier."

00:27:56.508 --> 00:27:57.576
You are exactly right.

00:27:57.576 --> 00:27:59.545
I think French always

00:27:59.545 --> 00:28:00.946
consider that they have

00:28:00.946 --> 00:28:02.748
been betrayed since maybe

00:28:02.748 --> 00:28:04.082
fifteen years about.

00:28:04.082 --> 00:28:07.185
They don't believe in politicians

00:28:07.185 --> 00:28:08.954
anymore...really, really...really.

00:28:08.954 --> 00:28:11.623
This question of betrayal is

00:28:11.623 --> 00:28:12.891
very important, because

00:28:12.891 --> 00:28:16.962
we had such an increase of

00:28:16.962 --> 00:28:17.963
extreme party in France

00:28:17.963 --> 00:28:18.964
like in Europe, but in France

00:28:18.964 --> 00:28:20.766
we had the National French

00:28:20.766 --> 00:28:23.969
gaining 20% in the election.

00:28:23.969 --> 00:28:25.103
This is the first time

00:28:25.103 --> 00:28:26.104
it's so high

00:28:26.104 --> 00:28:28.807
and this is I think the

00:28:28.807 --> 00:28:29.708
very, very, the first

00:28:29.708 --> 00:28:31.643
symptom of this crisis.

00:28:31.643 --> 00:28:37.983
We have France- which is not

00:28:37.983 --> 00:28:40.986
believing in Europe anymore,

00:28:40.986 --> 00:28:41.987
in globalization.

00:28:41.987 --> 00:28:43.822
They want to protect again,

00:28:43.822 --> 00:28:44.489
and go back to

00:28:44.489 --> 00:28:46.258
France and protect

00:28:46.258 --> 00:28:48.627
itself...and Europe is

00:28:48.627 --> 00:28:51.196
seen as danger.

00:28:51.196 --> 00:28:53.298
Before it was Asia,

00:28:53.298 --> 00:28:55.000
it was China...and now it's

00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:56.802
Europe, it's Europe.

