00:38:20.231 --> 00:38:21.599
that there are always good

00:38:21.599 --> 00:38:22.600
times, and there's alway

00:38:22.600 --> 00:38:24.302
bad times because of

00:38:24.302 --> 00:38:25.904
business cycles or

00:38:25.904 --> 00:38:26.538
economic cycles.

00:38:26.538 --> 00:38:27.972
That's why so many people

00:38:27.972 --> 00:38:29.741
were misled into thinking

00:38:29.741 --> 00:38:30.742
that the market will only

00:38:30.742 --> 00:38:32.076
continue growing.

00:38:32.076 --> 00:38:32.744
That's why so much money

00:38:32.744 --> 00:38:34.846
was pumped into the Greek

00:38:34.846 --> 00:38:37.749
economy. That's why so

00:38:37.749 --> 00:38:39.384
many people did not see

00:38:39.384 --> 00:38:40.819
this crisis coming in

00:38:40.819 --> 00:38:41.819
the first place. 		

00:38:47.091 --> 00:38:49.394
I think it's known as we all know...

00:38:49.394 --> 00:38:51.296
on a globalized world like as

00:38:51.296 --> 00:38:54.365
the subprime mortgage

00:38:54.365 --> 00:38:55.366
crisis that started in the

00:38:55.366 --> 00:38:56.568
United States and moved

00:38:56.568 --> 00:38:57.569
into Europe. I think that

00:38:57.569 --> 00:38:58.570
in all likely chances that

00:38:58.570 --> 00:39:00.271
the current Euro crisis

00:39:00.271 --> 00:39:03.541
may spread out- not to all,

00:39:03.541 --> 00:39:05.643
into the Atlantic but also

00:39:05.643 --> 00:39:07.645
into the developing

00:39:07.645 --> 00:39:08.947
countries...in my view,

00:39:08.947 --> 00:39:10.815
it's like a real prospect.

00:39:10.815 --> 00:39:11.816
But what I think the

00:39:11.816 --> 00:39:13.284
real crisis for the U.S.

00:39:13.284 --> 00:39:15.286
is- is that the level of

00:39:15.286 --> 00:39:17.121
economic shock to the world.

00:39:17.121 --> 00:39:18.122
If Europe goes down,

00:39:18.122 --> 00:39:19.123
we'll push the U.S.

00:39:19.123 --> 00:39:22.627
recovery back down even in

00:39:22.627 --> 00:39:23.828
to double-dipping back

00:39:23.828 --> 00:39:24.929
into recession.

00:39:24.929 --> 00:39:27.165
And what that means is then

00:39:27.165 --> 00:39:29.200
it's very difficult then for

00:39:29.200 --> 00:39:30.201
the U.S. to recover,

00:39:30.201 --> 00:39:31.469
because we have jobless

00:39:31.469 --> 00:39:34.472
recoveries. And if the

00:39:34.472 --> 00:39:36.975
U.S. can't start people

00:39:36.975 --> 00:39:39.477
again into jobs...it won't

00:39:39.477 --> 00:39:41.012
solve its debt crisis;

00:39:41.012 --> 00:39:42.981
it won't start being

00:39:42.981 --> 00:39:43.982
productive again. 		

00:39:44.983 --> 00:39:47.885
Phillip, I want to get to

00:39:47.885 --> 00:39:49.554
the point where I think that

00:39:49.554 --> 00:39:51.990
we agreed that the crisis

00:39:51.990 --> 00:39:55.026
we are facing- it's also

00:39:55.026 --> 00:39:57.829
primarily a productive crisis.

00:39:57.829 --> 00:39:59.998
From that point-

00:39:59.998 --> 00:40:00.999
and I think that's not

00:40:00.999 --> 00:40:02.900
part of the solution,

00:40:02.900 --> 00:40:05.970
for this crisis- should also

00:40:05.970 --> 00:40:07.705
be solving the

00:40:07.705 --> 00:40:10.241
productivity crisis.

00:40:10.241 --> 00:40:12.343
What we saw happening

00:40:12.343 --> 00:40:15.146
was exactly the opposite.

00:40:15.146 --> 00:40:18.616
The fact that most of the

00:40:18.616 --> 00:40:21.019
solutions...the portrayed

00:40:21.019 --> 00:40:23.488
solution was more on the

00:40:23.488 --> 00:40:24.856
consumer side of the balance.

00:40:24.856 --> 00:40:27.025
So like...we add the problem

00:40:27.025 --> 00:40:29.360
like the sub-prime mortgages,

00:40:29.360 --> 00:40:31.963
and there were needs.

00:40:31.963 --> 00:40:34.265
And we tried to solve

00:40:34.265 --> 00:40:37.035
those needs by artificially

00:40:37.035 --> 00:40:40.405
responding to the demands-

00:40:40.405 --> 00:40:41.873
rather than answering

00:40:41.873 --> 00:40:42.874
the main causes. 		

00:40:42.874 --> 00:40:44.142
I think that's completely

00:40:44.142 --> 00:40:46.377
right...and I think that's

00:40:46.377 --> 00:40:47.378
what's happened is the

00:40:47.378 --> 00:40:48.613
short-tem electoral cycle

00:40:48.613 --> 00:40:50.682
that we have prevents

00:40:50.682 --> 00:40:53.484
long-term solutions.

00:40:53.484 --> 00:40:54.485
It seems like there's

00:40:54.485 --> 00:40:55.486
quite a bit of corruption

00:40:55.486 --> 00:40:56.554
involved. It's all about

00:40:56.554 --> 00:40:58.122
what they personally want.

00:40:58.122 --> 00:41:00.158
I think my generation is

00:41:00.158 --> 00:41:01.326
pretty angry about the

00:41:01.326 --> 00:41:02.327
amount of debt that we're

00:41:02.327 --> 00:41:03.328
going to be shouldering.

00:41:03.328 --> 00:41:04.329
They're trying to make

00:41:04.329 --> 00:41:05.330
sure that they're making

00:41:05.330 --> 00:41:06.331
the popular choices, rather

00:41:06.331 --> 00:41:07.999
than necessarily making

00:41:07.999 --> 00:41:09.667
the hard correct choice.

00:41:09.667 --> 00:41:11.669
...a culture of borrowing.

00:41:15.006 --> 00:41:16.007
There's been a lot of

00:41:16.007 --> 00:41:17.008
focus on the European

00:41:17.008 --> 00:41:18.509
debt crisis where countries

00:41:18.509 --> 00:41:19.510
like Greece are on the

00:41:19.510 --> 00:41:21.012
brink of bankruptcy.

00:41:21.012 --> 00:41:22.013
But what about the

00:41:22.013 --> 00:41:24.148
United States- home of

00:41:24.148 --> 00:41:26.017
the dollar, the world's

00:41:26.017 --> 00:41:27.552
reserve currency?

00:41:27.552 --> 00:41:29.354
I'm in Washington, D.C.

00:41:29.354 --> 00:41:31.189
to find out.

00:41:35.360 --> 00:41:37.662
Today, the U. S. Government

00:41:37.662 --> 00:41:39.564
is spending over

00:41:39.564 --> 00:41:42.200
a $1.40 for every $1

00:41:42.200 --> 00:41:43.534
that it takes in in revenue.

00:41:43.534 --> 00:41:45.903
Today, the federal government

00:41:45.903 --> 00:41:47.939
has accumulated liabilities

00:41:47.939 --> 00:41:49.040
and unfunded obligations

00:41:49.040 --> 00:41:53.544
of over $550,000

00:41:53.544 --> 00:41:55.747
per household...

00:41:55.747 --> 00:41:58.416
and growing rapidly.

00:42:00.918 --> 00:42:01.919
This is David Walker.

00:42:01.919 --> 00:42:03.921
As long-time head of the

00:42:03.921 --> 00:42:05.289
U. S. General Accounting Office,

00:42:05.289 --> 00:42:06.924
few people know U.S. Government

00:42:06.924 --> 00:42:09.093
finances better than he does.

00:42:09.093 --> 00:42:11.229
For the past few years,

00:42:11.229 --> 00:42:13.097
he's been on a fiscal tour

00:42:13.097 --> 00:42:14.098
all across America

00:42:14.098 --> 00:42:15.500
talking about the

00:42:15.500 --> 00:42:17.502
financial state of the union.

00:42:17.502 --> 00:42:18.503
The United States

00:42:18.503 --> 00:42:21.472
is not Greece but then again,

00:42:21.472 --> 00:42:22.473
Greece is the

00:42:22.473 --> 00:42:23.775
cradle of democracy;

00:42:23.775 --> 00:42:25.009
it was once the greatest

00:42:25.009 --> 00:42:26.611
civilization on earth.

00:42:26.611 --> 00:42:27.879
It once controlled most of

00:42:27.879 --> 00:42:30.248
the known world,

00:42:30.248 --> 00:42:31.749
and Greece is now a mere

00:42:31.749 --> 00:42:32.884
shadow of itself-

00:42:32.884 --> 00:42:34.519
because it strayed from

00:42:34.519 --> 00:42:35.520
the principles and values

00:42:35.520 --> 00:42:36.587
that made it great.

00:42:36.587 --> 00:42:37.655
And Greece has got somebody

00:42:37.655 --> 00:42:40.525
to bail it out - the United States

00:42:40.525 --> 00:42:41.526
does not.

00:42:44.028 --> 00:42:45.530
Financial literacy is a

00:42:45.530 --> 00:42:46.330
particular problem in the

00:42:46.330 --> 00:42:48.566
United States- and it's even a

00:42:48.566 --> 00:42:50.034
bigger problem in the

00:42:50.034 --> 00:42:51.169
congress of the United States.

00:42:51.169 --> 00:42:53.271
There's no way

00:42:53.271 --> 00:42:54.439
that an American family

00:42:54.439 --> 00:42:56.174
or an American corporation

00:42:56.174 --> 00:42:57.508
could run its finances

00:42:57.508 --> 00:42:59.477
like the U.S. government.

00:42:59.477 --> 00:43:01.179
Too many of our elected

00:43:01.179 --> 00:43:02.180
officials, no matter how

00:43:02.180 --> 00:43:03.181
well- intended, are career

00:43:03.181 --> 00:43:05.483
politicians; they're human

00:43:05.483 --> 00:43:06.951
beings. They don't want to

00:43:06.951 --> 00:43:08.052
lose their job.

00:43:08.052 --> 00:43:09.053
A lot of them think that the

00:43:09.053 --> 00:43:10.688
people can't handle the truth,

00:43:10.688 --> 00:43:12.623
and so they don't tell

00:43:12.623 --> 00:43:13.624
them the truth. A lot of

00:43:13.624 --> 00:43:15.259
them don't have answers to

00:43:15.259 --> 00:43:16.260
these problems or, if they

00:43:16.260 --> 00:43:17.261
do have answers, they

00:43:17.261 --> 00:43:18.796
involve tough choices.

00:43:23.868 --> 00:43:24.869
Public pressure is

00:43:24.869 --> 00:43:25.870
critical because

00:43:25.870 --> 00:43:27.905
ultimately a vast majority

00:43:27.905 --> 00:43:28.906
of current elected

00:43:28.906 --> 00:43:29.907
officials are career

00:43:29.907 --> 00:43:31.609
politicians, and they want

00:43:31.609 --> 00:43:32.677
to keep their job.

00:43:32.677 --> 00:43:35.279
And if the public pressures them

00:43:35.279 --> 00:43:36.280
to act and holds them

00:43:36.280 --> 00:43:38.516
accountable for failing to act,

00:43:38.516 --> 00:43:41.118
then they will ultimately

00:43:41.118 --> 00:43:43.988
change...because many of

00:43:43.988 --> 00:43:45.022
their top priorities is to

00:43:45.022 --> 00:43:46.557
keep their job.

00:43:46.557 --> 00:43:48.025
There are a number of

00:43:48.025 --> 00:43:49.527
common denominators between

00:43:49.527 --> 00:43:51.762
countries, and some of the

00:43:51.762 --> 00:43:52.763
challenges that exist at

00:43:52.763 --> 00:43:54.298
the federal, state and

00:43:54.298 --> 00:43:55.366
local level here in the

00:43:55.366 --> 00:43:56.567
United States.

00:43:56.567 --> 00:43:58.536
In many cases, governments

00:43:58.536 --> 00:43:59.470
have grown too big,

00:43:59.470 --> 00:44:01.472
promised too much, and

00:44:01.472 --> 00:44:04.408
waited too long to restructure.

00:44:04.408 --> 00:44:06.344
I think we just don't know

00:44:06.344 --> 00:44:07.311
how to use money.

00:44:07.311 --> 00:44:08.312
I know that people my age

00:44:08.312 --> 00:44:09.313
never expect to get

00:44:09.313 --> 00:44:11.115
Social Security benefits.

00:44:11.115 --> 00:44:13.484
Hopeful, but I wouldn't

00:44:13.484 --> 00:44:15.820
say very optimistic.

00:44:19.590 --> 00:44:20.591
A lot of people claim that

00:44:20.591 --> 00:44:22.527
the problem is still the slack

00:44:22.527 --> 00:44:24.228
capacity, unused workers.

00:44:24.228 --> 00:44:26.097
Why not just increase

00:44:26.097 --> 00:44:28.633
demand, employ all those

00:44:28.633 --> 00:44:29.634
workers; put those

00:44:29.634 --> 00:44:31.402
factories back to work ...

00:44:31.402 --> 00:44:33.004
Well, it's important to

00:44:33.004 --> 00:44:34.005
look at the cases that

00:44:34.005 --> 00:44:35.006
actually have been working.

00:44:35.006 --> 00:44:36.741
For example, take Sweden.

00:44:36.741 --> 00:44:38.576
We have decreased taxes,

00:44:38.576 --> 00:44:40.545
we have deregulated,

00:44:40.545 --> 00:44:42.213
and we have cut down

00:44:42.213 --> 00:44:43.214
on government spending

00:44:43.214 --> 00:44:44.048
and in 2011

00:44:44.048 --> 00:44:46.517
we made a budget surplus

00:44:46.517 --> 00:44:48.586
of 10 billion dollars.

00:44:48.586 --> 00:44:50.254
A single data point, right?

00:44:50.254 --> 00:44:51.255
Look at these other countries:

00:44:51.255 --> 00:44:53.257
Greece, Spain, Italy

00:44:53.257 --> 00:44:54.258
- they're all depressed.

00:44:54.258 --> 00:44:56.661
The problem is slack capacity...

00:44:56.661 --> 00:44:59.230
excess capacity....too many

00:44:59.230 --> 00:45:00.164
workers unemployed.

00:45:00.164 --> 00:45:01.165
Let's put 'em back to work.

00:45:01.165 --> 00:45:03.234
How do you get workers back

00:45:03.234 --> 00:45:04.235
into the employment ranks?

00:45:04.235 --> 00:45:05.236
You gotta increase demand

00:45:05.236 --> 00:45:06.237
for what they do.

00:45:06.237 --> 00:45:06.938
The only way to increase

00:45:06.938 --> 00:45:07.939
demand for what they do is for

00:45:07.939 --> 00:45:08.940
government to spend more,

00:45:08.940 --> 00:45:10.441
because the private sector

00:45:10.441 --> 00:45:12.877
isn't doing it.

00:45:12.877 --> 00:45:13.878
Well, this is the things that

00:45:13.878 --> 00:45:14.912
Keynesians always say:

00:45:14.912 --> 00:45:17.582
Just pump more money into

00:45:17.582 --> 00:45:18.583
the economy. But it's

00:45:18.583 --> 00:45:19.584
important for us to look

00:45:19.584 --> 00:45:21.619
at all those times we have

00:45:21.619 --> 00:45:22.587
implemented these kinds of

00:45:22.587 --> 00:45:24.689
theories and the results

00:45:24.689 --> 00:45:25.690
have always been devastating.

00:45:25.690 --> 00:45:26.657
Japan in the 90s,

00:45:26.657 --> 00:45:29.293
the U.S. in '01 and '08.

00:45:29.293 --> 00:45:30.294
What we do need is

00:45:30.294 --> 00:45:31.729
free man, free markets

00:45:31.729 --> 00:45:33.331
and productivity.

00:45:33.331 --> 00:45:35.333
We as persons are good,

00:45:35.333 --> 00:45:36.267
we can create things.

00:45:36.267 --> 00:45:38.002
But we can't do it when

00:45:38.002 --> 00:45:40.304
we are...buried under a burden

00:45:40.304 --> 00:45:41.973
of government regulations.

00:45:41.973 --> 00:45:42.974
Look, all that's fine.

00:45:42.974 --> 00:45:43.908
But when we have

00:45:43.908 --> 00:45:44.909
massive unemployment,

00:45:44.909 --> 00:45:47.078
massive excess capacity,

00:45:47.078 --> 00:45:48.613
none of that's going to

00:45:48.613 --> 00:45:50.615
work unless demand is

00:45:50.615 --> 00:45:51.616
increased- and government's

00:45:51.616 --> 00:45:52.617
the only agency

00:45:52.617 --> 00:45:53.618
that can get demand

00:45:53.618 --> 00:45:54.685
throughout the entire

00:45:54.685 --> 00:45:56.354
economy. Well, is there

00:45:56.354 --> 00:45:58.022
any limit on exactly how

00:45:58.022 --> 00:45:59.023
much debt we will put on

00:45:59.023 --> 00:45:59.957
our children and our

00:45:59.957 --> 00:46:01.459
grandchildren before we

00:46:01.459 --> 00:46:02.727
realize that this way of

00:46:02.727 --> 00:46:03.728
thought is not working?

00:46:03.728 --> 00:46:05.963
Is there any hope the

00:46:05.963 --> 00:46:06.964
situation, we will not, we

00:46:06.964 --> 00:46:07.965
will all be Greece in

00:46:07.965 --> 00:46:10.434
15, 10, 5 years?

00:46:10.434 --> 00:46:12.036
During the last two months,

00:46:12.036 --> 00:46:14.338
I have met more immigrants

00:46:14.338 --> 00:46:16.407
from Ireland, Greece, Spain,

00:46:16.407 --> 00:46:17.408
in Stockholm, in Sweden...

00:46:17.408 --> 00:46:19.243
than I have during my

00:46:19.243 --> 00:46:20.244
entire life before.

00:46:20.244 --> 00:46:22.246
Is this witness of a

00:46:22.246 --> 00:46:23.247
well-functioning idea, of

00:46:23.247 --> 00:46:25.316
a good solution to a very

00:46:25.316 --> 00:46:26.317
big problem? Maybe Ireland

00:46:26.317 --> 00:46:27.318
is not spending enough

00:46:27.318 --> 00:46:29.987
money. Maybe they...

00:46:29.987 --> 00:46:30.988
the money supply...should

00:46:30.988 --> 00:46:33.024
increase in Ireland.

00:46:33.024 --> 00:46:36.027
Maybe fiscal deficits in Ireland

00:46:36.027 --> 00:46:37.828
should rise. Let me ask

00:46:37.828 --> 00:46:38.829
you about a more specific

00:46:38.829 --> 00:46:39.830
problem though.

00:46:39.830 --> 00:46:40.831
So you know, we have

00:46:40.831 --> 00:46:41.832
these problems with banks here,

00:46:41.832 --> 00:46:44.502
and in the U. S.

00:46:44.502 --> 00:46:45.503
Surely, the only way we can

00:46:45.503 --> 00:46:47.805
save the banks, are,

00:46:47.805 --> 00:46:51.242
is through, more...

00:46:51.242 --> 00:46:52.410
government support

00:46:52.410 --> 00:46:53.411
for the banks.

00:46:53.411 --> 00:46:54.412
Well, once again,

00:46:54.412 --> 00:46:55.413
we can look to

00:46:55.413 --> 00:46:56.814
a very recent example.

00:46:56.814 --> 00:46:59.016
The European Central Bank

00:46:59.016 --> 00:47:00.751
has issued one trillion Euros,

00:47:00.751 --> 00:47:02.486
in the liquidity means

00:47:02.486 --> 00:47:03.487
to the European banks.

00:47:03.487 --> 00:47:04.889
And what happened was that

00:47:04.889 --> 00:47:05.890
Spanish bonds went down

00:47:05.890 --> 00:47:08.059
for about one month,

00:47:08.059 --> 00:47:09.060
and then it went right up

00:47:09.060 --> 00:47:10.061
again because this is not

00:47:10.061 --> 00:47:11.095
a sustainable way of

00:47:11.095 --> 00:47:12.330
solv...solving the

00:47:12.330 --> 00:47:14.899
solvency issue in Europe.

00:47:14.899 --> 00:47:15.900
Isn't the problem though

00:47:15.900 --> 00:47:16.901
austerity? Austerity is

00:47:16.901 --> 00:47:19.537
sweeping across Europe,

00:47:19.537 --> 00:47:20.538
and austerity is what's

00:47:20.538 --> 00:47:22.340
keeping the economies from

00:47:22.340 --> 00:47:23.341
growing, it's what's

00:47:23.341 --> 00:47:25.209
keeping the banks in trouble.

00:47:25.209 --> 00:47:26.210
We just have to

00:47:26.210 --> 00:47:27.211
open the spigots, all this

00:47:27.211 --> 00:47:28.846
austerity stuff, this is

00:47:28.846 --> 00:47:30.347
old-fashioned economics.

00:47:30.347 --> 00:47:31.348
We've learned, since

00:47:31.348 --> 00:47:32.983
Keynes, that we need

00:47:32.983 --> 00:47:34.752
new stuff, spending.

00:47:34.752 --> 00:47:35.753
Well...there's been a lot

00:47:35.753 --> 00:47:36.754
of talking about austerity

00:47:36.754 --> 00:47:38.589
in Europe, in Spain and

00:47:38.589 --> 00:47:41.125
other countries, but if we

00:47:41.125 --> 00:47:42.526
really look, what kind of

00:47:42.526 --> 00:47:43.527
measures have been

00:47:43.527 --> 00:47:44.528
implemented? I haven't

00:47:44.528 --> 00:47:45.730
seen much austerity, not really.

00:47:45.730 --> 00:47:47.732
America's still in

00:47:47.732 --> 00:47:48.733
pretty bad straights;

00:47:48.733 --> 00:47:49.734
the unemployment rate

00:47:49.734 --> 00:47:51.602
remains stubbornly high.

00:47:51.602 --> 00:47:53.804
Shouldn't we spend more in America?

00:47:53.804 --> 00:47:55.339
Isn't the Keynesian remedy

00:47:55.339 --> 00:47:56.340
appropriate for the

00:47:56.340 --> 00:47:57.575
United States at least?

00:47:57.575 --> 00:47:59.376
Well, however we twist and turn

00:47:59.376 --> 00:48:01.245
this...we has to reach the

00:48:01.245 --> 00:48:02.246
conclusion that this is

00:48:02.246 --> 00:48:03.714
a crisis of productivity.

00:48:03.714 --> 00:48:04.715
It's a crisis of

00:48:04.715 --> 00:48:06.517
living over our means.

00:48:06.517 --> 00:48:08.853
If the United States wants to

00:48:08.853 --> 00:48:10.321
go down the European path,

00:48:10.321 --> 00:48:12.289
I would suggest...stimulants,

00:48:12.289 --> 00:48:13.791
and I would suggest the

00:48:13.791 --> 00:48:14.792
Keynesian way of doing it.

00:48:14.792 --> 00:48:16.560
But if you actually want

00:48:16.560 --> 00:48:17.561
to have a brighter future

00:48:17.561 --> 00:48:18.429
for your children,

00:48:18.429 --> 00:48:19.430
I suggest some more saving

00:48:19.430 --> 00:48:20.431
and some more working.

00:48:20.965 --> 00:48:21.966
Seems we're in a dilemma

00:48:21.966 --> 00:48:25.102
here....that austerity,

00:48:25.102 --> 00:48:25.970
at least to me,

00:48:25.970 --> 00:48:26.971
seems inevitable in most parts

00:48:26.971 --> 00:48:28.639
of Europe. On the other hand,

00:48:28.639 --> 00:48:29.640
you have people in

00:48:29.640 --> 00:48:30.641
the streets, also in many

00:48:30.641 --> 00:48:31.976
countries protesting

00:48:31.976 --> 00:48:32.977
against this, and it's

00:48:32.977 --> 00:48:34.945
also understandable.

00:48:34.945 --> 00:48:36.180
How do we solve that?

00:48:36.180 --> 00:48:38.082
It's a huge democratic problem,

00:48:38.082 --> 00:48:39.083
I think. Tocqueville

00:48:39.083 --> 00:48:40.084
supposedly said that

00:48:40.084 --> 00:48:41.952
democracy can only exist

00:48:41.952 --> 00:48:43.554
until the voters discover

00:48:43.554 --> 00:48:44.555
that they can vote for

00:48:44.555 --> 00:48:45.556
themselves, not just from

00:48:45.556 --> 00:48:46.290
the public treasury.

00:48:46.290 --> 00:48:48.259
And I think we see that

00:48:48.259 --> 00:48:50.161
that has created the addiction

00:48:50.161 --> 00:48:52.062
to public benefits...entitlements

00:48:52.062 --> 00:48:53.664
that we see in Europe.

00:48:53.664 --> 00:48:55.232
So now in Denmark,

00:48:55.232 --> 00:48:57.001
we have the tax authorities

00:48:57.001 --> 00:48:58.469
who are able to access your

00:48:58.469 --> 00:49:00.271
phone records... Really?

00:49:00.271 --> 00:49:01.438
...without a court

00:49:01.438 --> 00:49:02.807
warrant, without

00:49:02.807 --> 00:49:03.874
reasonable suspicion.

00:49:03.874 --> 00:49:04.675
If you are a pensioner,

00:49:04.675 --> 00:49:05.676
you have to report it to

00:49:05.676 --> 00:49:06.444
your municipality.

00:49:06.444 --> 00:49:07.444
If you leave your country

00:49:07.444 --> 00:49:08.946
for long periods...most

00:49:08.946 --> 00:49:10.881
municipalities have websites,

00:49:10.881 --> 00:49:11.882
hotlines, where you can

00:49:11.882 --> 00:49:12.883
call your, you know,

00:49:12.883 --> 00:49:14.685
and report your neighbor

00:49:14.685 --> 00:49:15.686
if you suspect them

00:49:15.686 --> 00:49:16.887
of receiving entitlements

00:49:16.887 --> 00:49:18.622
that they don't have the right to.

00:49:18.622 --> 00:49:19.623
It seems like the

00:49:19.623 --> 00:49:20.724
financial big brother is

00:49:20.724 --> 00:49:21.725
watching all over you.

00:49:21.725 --> 00:49:23.194
Yes, and you know, there's

00:49:23.194 --> 00:49:24.195
no uproar, there's no

00:49:24.195 --> 00:49:26.063
revolt about this because

00:49:26.063 --> 00:49:27.164
the system that we have

00:49:27.164 --> 00:49:28.933
created...creates this

00:49:28.933 --> 00:49:31.135
perverse incentive for

00:49:31.135 --> 00:49:32.136
the citizens to care about

00:49:32.136 --> 00:49:33.537
what their neighbors are doing.

00:49:33.537 --> 00:49:34.538
Not out of compassion-

00:49:34.538 --> 00:49:36.540
but out of, you know,

00:49:36.540 --> 00:49:37.541
self-interest

00:49:37.541 --> 00:49:38.309
that you don't want someone

00:49:38.309 --> 00:49:39.677
else to abuse the system.

00:49:39.677 --> 00:49:40.678
So in many ways we

00:49:40.678 --> 00:49:40.778
have created this

00:49:40.778 --> 00:49:43.247
Byzantine Kafkaesque...

00:49:43.247 --> 00:49:44.949
system of

00:49:44.949 --> 00:49:45.950
laws and regulations

00:49:45.950 --> 00:49:47.251
that in some ways

00:49:47.251 --> 00:49:48.385
subject the average Danish citizens

00:49:48.385 --> 00:49:50.321
to measures that we know,

00:49:50.321 --> 00:49:51.322
that we knew in the old

00:49:51.322 --> 00:49:52.056
Eastern Germany.

00:49:52.056 --> 00:49:54.158
Hopefully one day we will be

00:49:54.158 --> 00:49:55.993
out of this crisis situation.

00:49:55.993 --> 00:49:58.128
Brussels will need to

00:49:58.128 --> 00:50:00.497
think very hard as to how

00:50:00.497 --> 00:50:01.498
to prevent these crises

00:50:01.498 --> 00:50:02.499
from happening over and

00:50:02.499 --> 00:50:04.568
over again. And to me,

00:50:04.568 --> 00:50:05.569
as an economist, it seems

00:50:05.569 --> 00:50:07.238
that the only way out is

00:50:07.238 --> 00:50:09.974
to have, actually further

00:50:09.974 --> 00:50:11.275
integration in Europe,

00:50:11.275 --> 00:50:13.644
is to have a unified fiscal

00:50:13.644 --> 00:50:14.645
and budget policy- because

00:50:14.645 --> 00:50:16.213
the imbalances between

00:50:16.213 --> 00:50:18.015
these countries are so big.

00:50:18.015 --> 00:50:19.016
The European Union,

00:50:19.016 --> 00:50:20.017
the Commission, its

00:50:20.017 --> 00:50:22.386
institutions, do not have

00:50:22.386 --> 00:50:23.387
legitimacy in the European

00:50:23.387 --> 00:50:25.589
populations, and also,

00:50:25.589 --> 00:50:27.424
you know, if you live in Ohio

00:50:27.424 --> 00:50:28.425
and Pennsylvania you feel

00:50:28.425 --> 00:50:30.294
American, but if you live

00:50:30.294 --> 00:50:31.295
in Greece and Denmark-

00:50:31.295 --> 00:50:32.296
you don't feel...you don't

00:50:32.296 --> 00:50:33.430
have that same bond.

00:50:33.430 --> 00:50:35.032
I think that it was a

00:50:35.032 --> 00:50:37.234
mistake to build a massive

00:50:37.234 --> 00:50:38.235
political union upon

00:50:38.235 --> 00:50:40.237
basically the internal market.

00:50:40.237 --> 00:50:41.338
The internal market has

00:50:41.338 --> 00:50:43.107
worked wonderfully in creating

00:50:43.107 --> 00:50:46.911
wealth, and democracy...

00:50:46.911 --> 00:50:48.979
securing that in a continent

00:50:48.979 --> 00:50:50.915
with a very bloody history.

00:50:50.915 --> 00:50:51.916
But we simply

00:50:51.916 --> 00:50:52.716
do not have that

00:50:52.716 --> 00:50:55.185
shared history and culture

00:50:55.185 --> 00:50:56.120
that is necessary for a

00:50:56.120 --> 00:50:57.254
centralized political

00:50:57.254 --> 00:51:00.057
union, and therefore

00:51:00.057 --> 00:51:01.492
I think it's a huge mistake,

00:51:01.492 --> 00:51:03.093
and it undermines the very

00:51:03.093 --> 00:51:04.461
purpose of the EU.

00:51:04.461 --> 00:51:05.462
So you're suggesting not a

00:51:05.462 --> 00:51:06.463
step forward in

00:51:06.463 --> 00:51:07.464
integration, but maybe

00:51:07.464 --> 00:51:08.465
even a step backwards

00:51:08.465 --> 00:51:10.034
towards sustaining the

00:51:10.034 --> 00:51:11.035
four freedoms between

00:51:11.035 --> 00:51:12.002
these nations?

00:51:12.002 --> 00:51:14.505
Yes. I would...I would advocate

00:51:14.505 --> 00:51:17.141
a more simple model that was

00:51:17.141 --> 00:51:18.142
based largely on the four

00:51:18.142 --> 00:51:20.010
freedoms- and not for the

00:51:20.010 --> 00:51:21.612
political integration, and not

00:51:21.612 --> 00:51:25.349
necessarily a common currency.

00:51:25.349 --> 00:51:26.350
What we're seeing

00:51:26.350 --> 00:51:27.952
with Europe and the

00:51:27.952 --> 00:51:31.188
U.S. is trillions of

00:51:31.188 --> 00:51:32.556
currency units created,

00:51:32.556 --> 00:51:36.060
and yet growth is stalling.

00:51:36.060 --> 00:51:37.061
So basically,

00:51:37.061 --> 00:51:38.028
instead of getting back to

00:51:38.028 --> 00:51:40.397
growth by production and

00:51:40.397 --> 00:51:42.733
reform and competitiveness-

00:51:42.733 --> 00:51:44.702
we're just printing new money,

00:51:44.702 --> 00:51:46.737
creating money out of thin air.

00:51:46.737 --> 00:51:48.172
And that creates

00:51:48.172 --> 00:51:49.173
these bubbles, because

00:51:49.173 --> 00:51:51.008
money ends up somewhere.

00:51:51.008 --> 00:51:52.009
It creates the financial

00:51:52.009 --> 00:51:53.377
bubbles which become very

00:51:53.377 --> 00:51:55.245
destructive and destabilizing.

00:51:55.245 --> 00:51:56.246
But all these

00:51:56.246 --> 00:51:57.247
other things that

00:51:57.247 --> 00:51:58.616
we're talking about in

00:51:58.616 --> 00:52:00.985
terms of overspending,

00:52:00.985 --> 00:52:01.986
over-indebtedness...

00:52:01.986 --> 00:52:02.987
So what do you think happens

00:52:02.987 --> 00:52:03.988
then, when we're in a

00:52:03.988 --> 00:52:04.989
crisis and we're trying to

00:52:04.989 --> 00:52:07.658
solve it by inflating the

00:52:07.658 --> 00:52:09.193
bubbles again, just

00:52:09.193 --> 00:52:11.829
creating new...more money?

00:52:11.829 --> 00:52:13.998
Ultimately, it just makes

00:52:13.998 --> 00:52:14.999
matters worse.

00:52:14.999 --> 00:52:17.901
It's understandable that it

00:52:17.901 --> 00:52:19.837
happens-but it's a kind of

00:52:19.837 --> 00:52:21.672
desperation. It would be

00:52:21.672 --> 00:52:23.207
something like giving

00:52:23.207 --> 00:52:24.308
steroids to an arthritic

00:52:24.308 --> 00:52:27.044
patient. It's a miracle

00:52:27.044 --> 00:52:28.645
drug to begin with-but if

00:52:28.645 --> 00:52:30.447
it's over-used, it becomes

00:52:30.447 --> 00:52:31.448
worse than the problem.

00:52:31.448 --> 00:52:33.217
But it's incredibly scary,

00:52:33.217 --> 00:52:34.218
because if we build

00:52:34.218 --> 00:52:35.986
the recovery...not with

00:52:35.986 --> 00:52:37.688
reform and competitiveness

00:52:37.688 --> 00:52:38.689
and real production,

00:52:38.689 --> 00:52:40.024
but just in printing

00:52:40.024 --> 00:52:41.025
more money, we create

00:52:41.025 --> 00:52:43.560
even more unsustainable bubbles.

00:52:43.560 --> 00:52:44.561
Where would that end in

00:52:44.561 --> 00:52:45.896
the future...in the long run?

00:52:45.896 --> 00:52:46.430
Absolutely...well,

00:52:46.430 --> 00:52:50.734
the worst part is likely

00:52:50.734 --> 00:52:52.469
to come in terms of the

00:52:52.469 --> 00:52:54.872
social instability.

00:52:54.872 --> 00:52:56.006
What we're seeing for

00:52:56.006 --> 00:52:58.575
the public in the U.S.-

00:52:58.575 --> 00:53:00.778
it will be a difficult time

00:53:00.778 --> 00:53:01.845
for a long time.

00:53:01.845 --> 00:53:03.347
I know that people my age

00:53:03.347 --> 00:53:04.448
never expect to get Social

00:53:04.448 --> 00:53:06.083
Security benefits.

00:53:06.083 --> 00:53:08.585
This bankruptcy will ruin

00:53:08.585 --> 00:53:10.254
our property taxes, which will

00:53:10.254 --> 00:53:12.356
ruin our schools-

00:53:12.356 --> 00:53:13.357
which ruins our future.

00:53:13.357 --> 00:53:15.092
It's about 20 percent of the

00:53:15.092 --> 00:53:16.960
people...of the population

00:53:16.960 --> 00:53:17.961
lost their job during the

00:53:17.961 --> 00:53:19.163
last five years.

00:53:19.163 --> 00:53:20.697
It could have been done so

00:53:20.697 --> 00:53:22.900
much better with a little bit

00:53:22.900 --> 00:53:24.068
of courage a civile,

00:53:24.068 --> 00:53:26.570
of civil courage...if you like.

00:53:26.570 --> 00:53:28.172
When I had my exams

00:53:28.172 --> 00:53:29.173
to get into the

00:53:29.173 --> 00:53:30.174
university, I was thinking

00:53:30.174 --> 00:53:32.810
that, "Wow! I'm going to

00:53:32.810 --> 00:53:33.944
become a pharmacist,

00:53:33.944 --> 00:53:35.512
I'm going to have a good job;

00:53:35.512 --> 00:53:36.947
I'm going to have a drugstore;

00:53:36.947 --> 00:53:39.583
I'm going to have a good life."

00:53:39.583 --> 00:53:44.054
And now...I just...I hope I

00:53:44.054 --> 00:53:46.423
get 30 Euros in 8 hours by

00:53:46.423 --> 00:53:48.592
becoming...by being a waitress.

00:53:48.592 --> 00:53:50.427
And I don't know

00:53:50.427 --> 00:53:50.694
what I will do

00:53:50.694 --> 00:53:53.263
...if we had referendum in France,

00:53:53.263 --> 00:53:55.332
I'm sure people rejected

00:53:55.332 --> 00:53:56.734
Europe. ...just to put it

00:53:56.734 --> 00:53:58.802
very simply, successful

00:53:58.802 --> 00:53:59.770
capitalists hate

00:53:59.770 --> 00:54:00.737
capitalism. The word

00:54:00.737 --> 00:54:02.906
austerity is now giving

00:54:02.906 --> 00:54:03.907
the creeps to pretty much

00:54:03.907 --> 00:54:04.908
all of Europe... But if

00:54:04.908 --> 00:54:05.909
you actually want to have

00:54:05.909 --> 00:54:06.910
a brighter future for your

00:54:06.910 --> 00:54:08.145
children, I suggest some

00:54:08.145 --> 00:54:09.179
more saving and some more

00:54:09.179 --> 00:54:10.180
working. A lot of

00:54:10.180 --> 00:54:12.149
people are scared about the

00:54:12.149 --> 00:54:13.484
future...especially young people.

00:54:13.484 --> 00:54:16.720
But you know...unfortunately,

00:54:16.720 --> 00:54:17.721
politicians don't get the story.

00:54:17.721 --> 00:54:18.856
They don't want to

00:54:18.856 --> 00:54:21.358
realize the severity of

00:54:21.358 --> 00:54:22.793
the problem; they don't

00:54:22.793 --> 00:54:23.861
want to do anything.

00:54:23.861 --> 00:54:24.962
They don't have the courage.

00:54:24.962 --> 00:54:26.630
Europe is today one of the

00:54:26.630 --> 00:54:28.532
richest continents in the world.

00:54:28.532 --> 00:54:29.533
And my hope...my

00:54:29.533 --> 00:54:31.902
dream is that Africa, and

00:54:31.902 --> 00:54:32.102
indeed my country,

00:54:32.102 --> 00:54:33.704
Mozambique, one day will

00:54:33.704 --> 00:54:35.672
become also wealthy.

00:54:35.672 --> 00:54:39.309
And we need to understand

00:54:39.309 --> 00:54:40.978
the deep causes of today's

00:54:40.978 --> 00:54:44.281
crisis, so that Africa and

00:54:44.281 --> 00:54:45.249
Mozambique can avoid the

00:54:45.249 --> 00:54:47.851
same mistakes that Europe

00:54:47.851 --> 00:54:48.852
is making today.

00:54:49.853 --> 00:54:52.055
In a way, it's not all gloomy.

00:54:52.055 --> 00:54:54.091
We've had 10 bad years of

00:54:54.091 --> 00:54:56.160
crisis, but at the same

00:54:56.160 --> 00:54:57.161
time we've probably

00:54:57.161 --> 00:54:58.395
created something like a

00:54:58.395 --> 00:54:59.463
quarter of all the wealth

00:54:59.463 --> 00:55:00.464
that mankind has ever

00:55:00.464 --> 00:55:02.466
created over those 10 years.

00:55:02.466 --> 00:55:03.133
Absolutely...and we

00:55:03.133 --> 00:55:05.135
have to be careful not to

00:55:05.135 --> 00:55:06.336
destroy that, because the

00:55:06.336 --> 00:55:08.338
market is the only source

00:55:08.338 --> 00:55:10.340
of widespread prosperity.

00:55:11.108 --> 00:55:12.109
You know...we're not

00:55:12.109 --> 00:55:13.944
talking about numbers when

00:55:13.944 --> 00:55:14.945
we're talking about this.

00:55:14.945 --> 00:55:15.946
It's really about people-

00:55:15.946 --> 00:55:17.614
it's about their dreams.

00:55:17.614 --> 00:55:18.615
It all comes down to that

00:55:18.615 --> 00:55:20.684
young woman I met in Greece.

00:55:20.684 --> 00:55:21.819
She wanted to own

00:55:21.819 --> 00:55:23.754
a drugstore, and now she's

00:55:23.754 --> 00:55:26.823
content just being a waitress.

00:55:26.823 --> 00:55:27.491
And our way of dealing

00:55:27.491 --> 00:55:28.825
with this crisis will

00:55:28.825 --> 00:55:29.826
decide the fate of her

00:55:29.826 --> 00:55:31.662
and millions like her.

